WEBVTT

1
00:03:58.507 --> 00:04:03.262
- Ready? You have your instructions.
- <i>Oui. monsieur.</i>

2
00:04:18.467 --> 00:04:20.981
Everything all right. Mrs Ho?

3
00:04:21.987 --> 00:04:24.023
Dinner will be ready at 7.30.

4
00:04:37.427 --> 00:04:39.736
- Good evening.
- I don't know if...

5
00:04:39.907 --> 00:04:43.502
You are expected. Colonel.
May I take your coat?

6
00:04:43.667 --> 00:04:47.216
- It is Colonel Mustard?
- No. that's not my name...

7
00:04:47.387 --> 00:04:52.541
Tonight. you may well feel obliged
to my employer for the use of an alias.

8
00:05:04.347 --> 00:05:09.137
- And who are you?
- Wadsworth. sir. The butler.

9
00:05:16.747 --> 00:05:20.262
Yvette. give the Colonel
anything he requires.

10
00:05:20.427 --> 00:05:23.260
Within reason. that is.

11
00:05:23.427 --> 00:05:25.497
Wadsworth. I was...

12
00:05:30.947 --> 00:05:33.097
Come in. madam. You are expected.

13
00:05:33.267 --> 00:05:37.180
- You know who I am?
- You are to be known as Mrs White.

14
00:05:37.347 --> 00:05:40.737
Yes. it said so in the letter. But why?

15
00:05:57.187 --> 00:06:01.897
May I introduce you?
Mrs White. this is Yvette. the maid.

16
00:06:02.067 --> 00:06:05.025
I see you know each other.

17
00:06:06.107 --> 00:06:07.426
- Hello.
- Hello.

18
00:06:41.507 --> 00:06:45.546
- Want a lift?
- Yes. please!

19
00:06:48.147 --> 00:06:53.426
- Thanks. I'm late for a dinner date.
- Me too. Where are you going?

20
00:06:53.587 --> 00:06:57.262
Let's see... hill house. off route 41.

21
00:06:57.427 --> 00:07:03.263
Wait. let me look. That's where I'm going.
I got a letter like this.

22
00:07:13.027 --> 00:07:16.906
- And this is Mrs Peacock.
- How do you do?

23
00:07:17.067 --> 00:07:22.380
Yvette. check dinner will be ready
as soon as all the guests have arrived.

24
00:07:37.667 --> 00:07:41.626
- Is this the address for Mr Boddy?
- You must be Mr Green.

25
00:07:41.787 --> 00:07:43.539
Sit!

26
00:07:43.707 --> 00:07:45.902
No... not you. sir.

27
00:07:52.307 --> 00:07:55.060
It should be just off there.

28
00:08:02.027 --> 00:08:04.461
That must be it.

29
00:08:06.187 --> 00:08:09.145
- Why has the car stopped?
- It's frightened.

30
00:08:56.627 --> 00:08:58.618
What a God-forsaken place!

31
00:09:02.387 --> 00:09:04.378
Professor Plum! Miss Scarlet!

32
00:09:04.547 --> 00:09:08.381
- I didn't know you were acquainted.
- We weren't.

33
00:09:13.427 --> 00:09:17.215
May I present Professor Plum
and miss Scarlet?

34
00:09:28.667 --> 00:09:31.465
You've each been addressed
by a pseudonym.

35
00:09:31.627 --> 00:09:35.779
Nobody here is being addressed
by their real name.

36
00:09:39.427 --> 00:09:41.622
Ah. dinner.

37
00:09:41.787 --> 00:09:46.417
I'm sorry. I'm a little accident-prone.

38
00:09:55.827 --> 00:10:00.617
You'll find your names
beside your places. Please be seated.

39
00:10:08.707 --> 00:10:11.824
- Is this place yours?
- No. sir. I'm a butler.

40
00:10:11.987 --> 00:10:14.785
- What exactly do you do?
- I buttle. sir.

41
00:10:14.947 --> 00:10:19.020
The butler is head of the kitchen
and dining-room. I keep things tidy.

42
00:10:19.187 --> 00:10:22.065
What's all this about. this dinner party?

43
00:10:22.227 --> 00:10:25.219
Ours not to reason why.
ours but to do and die.

44
00:10:25.387 --> 00:10:28.538
- Die?
- Merely quoting Tennyson. sir.

45
00:10:28.707 --> 00:10:34.304
I prefer Kipling. "The female of the
species is more deadly than the male."

46
00:10:34.467 --> 00:10:38.062
- You like Kipling?
- I'll eat anything.

47
00:10:38.787 --> 00:10:40.300
Soup.

48
00:10:40.467 --> 00:10:43.857
- For our host?
- For the seventh guest. Mr Boddy.

49
00:10:44.027 --> 00:10:46.985
- I thought Mr Boddy was our host.
- So did I.

50
00:10:47.147 --> 00:10:50.344
So. who is our host. Mr Wadsworth?

51
00:10:53.267 --> 00:10:56.418
- I want to start.
- Wait for the other guest.

52
00:10:56.587 --> 00:11:01.138
- I'll keep something warm for him.
- What did you have in mind?

53
00:11:30.867 --> 00:11:34.223
Well. someone's got to break the ice.
so why not me?

54
00:11:34.387 --> 00:11:37.265
I'm often a hostess.
for my husband's work.

55
00:11:37.427 --> 00:11:42.547
It's always hard. when new friends
meet for the first time. to get acquainted.

56
00:11:42.707 --> 00:11:45.619
so I'm prepared
to start the ball roiling.

57
00:11:45.787 --> 00:11:50.736
I have no idea why we're here.
why I'm here. what this place is about.

58
00:11:50.907 --> 00:11:54.377
but I am determined to enjoy myself.
I'm very intrigued.

59
00:11:54.547 --> 00:11:57.266
and this soup's delicious. isn't it?

60
00:12:00.067 --> 00:12:02.786
You are often a hostess
for your husband?

61
00:12:02.947 --> 00:12:08.340
Yes. it's an integral part of your life
when you are the wife of a...

62
00:12:08.507 --> 00:12:12.739
I forgot. we mustn't say who we are.
though I don't know why.

63
00:12:12.907 --> 00:12:16.582
- Don't you?
- I know who you are.

64
00:12:16.747 --> 00:12:18.897
- Will you tell?
- How do you know?

65
00:12:19.067 --> 00:12:20.944
I work in Washington. too.

66
00:12:21.107 --> 00:12:24.383
- So you're a politician's wife?
- Yes. I am.

67
00:12:24.547 --> 00:12:27.698
Come on. then. Who's your husband?

68
00:12:33.787 --> 00:12:37.223
- So what does your husband do?
- Nothing.

69
00:12:37.387 --> 00:12:42.381
- He lies around on his back all day.
- Sounds like hard work to me.

70
00:12:46.627 --> 00:12:48.618
I'm sorry!

71
00:12:50.667 --> 00:12:53.420
- I'm a little accident-prone.
- Watch it.

72
00:12:56.747 --> 00:12:59.136
<i>Excusez-moi.</i>

73
00:13:13.987 --> 00:13:18.185
- This is one of my favourite recipes.
- I know. madam.

74
00:13:21.107 --> 00:13:25.305
What do you do in Washington DC.
Mr Green?

75
00:13:25.467 --> 00:13:29.904
Come on! How can we get acquainted
if we say nothing about ourselves?

76
00:13:30.067 --> 00:13:32.217
Perhaps he doesn't want to.

77
00:13:32.387 --> 00:13:35.538
I don't know.
but if I wasn't making conversation

78
00:13:35.707 --> 00:13:38.858
we'd be sitting here
in an embarrassed silence.

79
00:13:39.027 --> 00:13:42.303
- Are you afraid of silence?
- Yes... no... why?

80
00:13:42.467 --> 00:13:46.062
You seem to suffer from what we call
"pressure of speech".

81
00:13:46.227 --> 00:13:48.218
Who's "we"? Are you a shrink?

82
00:13:48.387 --> 00:13:52.062
I do know a little
about psychological medicine. yes.

83
00:13:52.227 --> 00:13:54.582
- A doctor?
- But I don't practise.

84
00:13:54.747 --> 00:13:59.980
Practice makes perfect. Most men
need a little practice. don't you think?

85
00:14:00.147 --> 00:14:03.423
- So what do you do?
- I work for the united nations.

86
00:14:03.587 --> 00:14:05.703
Another politician!

87
00:14:05.867 --> 00:14:10.099
I work for a branch of the UNO.
WHO. the World Health Organisation.

88
00:14:10.267 --> 00:14:13.816
- What is your area of concern?
- Family planning.

89
00:14:13.987 --> 00:14:17.263
- Are you a real colonel?
- I am. sir.

90
00:14:17.427 --> 00:14:21.340
You're not going to mention
you also live in Washington DC?

91
00:14:21.507 --> 00:14:24.624
How did you know that?
Have we met before?

92
00:14:24.787 --> 00:14:28.336
I've seen you before.
You may not have seen me.

93
00:14:28.507 --> 00:14:31.624
- Do you live in Washington. too?
- I sure do.

94
00:14:31.787 --> 00:14:35.018
- Does anyone not live in Washington?
- I don't.

95
00:14:35.187 --> 00:14:39.499
But you work for the united nations.
a government job.

96
00:14:39.667 --> 00:14:43.580
Anyone not earn their living
from the government?

97
00:14:44.827 --> 00:14:49.025
Where's our host
and why have we been brought here?

98
00:14:53.987 --> 00:14:57.104
<i>Good evening.</i>
<i>You are eagerly awaited.</i>

99
00:14:58.067 --> 00:15:01.776
<i>- Locking me in? I'll take the key.</i>
- <i>Over my dead body. sir.</i>

100
00:15:01.947 --> 00:15:04.256
<i>- May I take your bag?</i>
<i>- No.</i>

101
00:15:04.427 --> 00:15:10.184
<i>- It contains evidence?</i>
<i>- Surprises. that's what it contains.</i>

102
00:15:11.147 --> 00:15:15.026
Ladies and gentlemen.
may I present Mr Boddy?

103
00:15:15.187 --> 00:15:17.860
- What are they doing here?
- Eating dinner.

104
00:15:18.027 --> 00:15:21.622
- Do sit down. Mr Boddy.
- Thanks.

105
00:15:23.867 --> 00:15:27.382
No. you can take that away. honey.

106
00:15:32.427 --> 00:15:37.057
I demand to know what's going on.
Why have we been dragged here?

107
00:15:37.227 --> 00:15:40.822
Well. I believe we all received a letter.

108
00:15:40.987 --> 00:15:44.423
My letter says. "it will be
to your advantage to be present.

109
00:15:44.587 --> 00:15:51.026
"because a Mr Boddy will end a certain
long-standing. painful. financial liability."

110
00:15:51.187 --> 00:15:54.224
- Signed. "a friend."
- I got a similar letter.

111
00:15:54.387 --> 00:15:58.539
- So did we. didn't we?
- I also received a letter.

112
00:15:58.707 --> 00:16:01.983
- No. Yvette. I just ate.
- You know her?

113
00:16:02.147 --> 00:16:05.184
We know each other. don't we. dear?

114
00:16:06.467 --> 00:16:09.265
Forgive me.
but was your letter the same?

115
00:16:09.427 --> 00:16:12.021
- No.
- I see.

116
00:16:14.067 --> 00:16:18.265
Can I interest any of you in fruit.
or dessert?

117
00:16:19.707 --> 00:16:23.063
I suggest we adjourn
for coffee and brandy.

118
00:16:23.227 --> 00:16:27.140
when I believe our unknown host
will reveal his intentions.

119
00:16:30.787 --> 00:16:36.305
- There's no one here.
- Please help yourselves and be seated.

120
00:16:45.107 --> 00:16:47.302
Mind if I smoke?

121
00:17:06.267 --> 00:17:10.180
I'm instructed to explain to you
what you all have in common.

122
00:17:10.347 --> 00:17:13.862
unless you would care to do the honours.
Mr Boddy?

123
00:17:14.027 --> 00:17:17.815
- Why? They know who I am?
- I don't think so.

124
00:17:17.987 --> 00:17:22.139
- It's a hoax. I suggest we all leave.
- You cannot leave this house!

125
00:17:22.307 --> 00:17:25.504
- No? Who's gonna stop me?
- There's no way out.

126
00:17:25.667 --> 00:17:28.135
The windows and doors are locked.

127
00:17:28.307 --> 00:17:32.505
- Outrageous! You can't imprison us!
- Ladies and gentlemen!

128
00:17:32.667 --> 00:17:36.819
Please return to the study.
Everything will be explained.

129
00:17:36.987 --> 00:17:38.864
You too. Mr Boddy.

130
00:17:39.067 --> 00:17:41.103
The other way!

131
00:17:48.627 --> 00:17:51.187
- You can't go that way.
- It's only glass.

132
00:18:14.587 --> 00:18:19.058
You all have one thing in common.
You're all being blackmailed.

133
00:18:19.227 --> 00:18:25.575
You have all been paying money to
someone who threatens to expose you.

134
00:18:25.747 --> 00:18:28.500
And none of you know
who's blackmailing you.

135
00:18:28.667 --> 00:18:32.262
Please! That's ridiculous.
Nobody could blackmail me.

136
00:18:32.427 --> 00:18:36.898
My life is an open book.
I've never done anything wrong.

137
00:18:37.067 --> 00:18:39.979
Anybody else wish to deny it?

138
00:18:44.467 --> 00:18:48.938
As everyone's in the same boat.
there's no harm in revealing details.

139
00:18:49.107 --> 00:18:52.816
And my instructions are to do so.
Thank you. Yvette.

140
00:18:59.587 --> 00:19:04.297
- Can't you spare us this humiliation?
- I'm sorry.

141
00:19:05.307 --> 00:19:08.379
Professor Plum.
You were a psychiatry Professor.

142
00:19:08.547 --> 00:19:12.540
helping paranoid. homicidal lunatics
with delusions of grandeur.

143
00:19:12.707 --> 00:19:15.540
- Now I work for the UN.
- The same job.

144
00:19:15.707 --> 00:19:17.698
You don't practise medicine.

145
00:19:17.907 --> 00:19:21.377
- His licence has been lifted.
- Why? What did he do?

146
00:19:21.547 --> 00:19:25.096
You know what doctors mustn't do
with patients? He did.

147
00:19:25.267 --> 00:19:30.387
- How disgusting!
- Are you making moral judgements?

148
00:19:31.827 --> 00:19:37.140
Can you justify taking bribes. for handing
your husband's vote to lobbyists?

149
00:19:37.307 --> 00:19:42.301
- Nothing wrong with paid consultancy.
- Not if it's publicly declared.

150
00:19:42.467 --> 00:19:48.463
But what if it's used greenbacks slipped
under the door of the men's room?

151
00:19:48.627 --> 00:19:51.016
- It stinks.
- Were you in the men's room?

152
00:19:51.187 --> 00:19:53.542
- It's true?
- It's a vicious lie.

153
00:19:53.707 --> 00:19:56.141
I'm sure we're glad to hear that.

154
00:19:56.307 --> 00:20:01.586
But you've paid blackmail for over a year
to keep it out of the papers.

155
00:20:01.747 --> 00:20:04.739
I'm being blackmailed
for something I didn't do.

156
00:20:04.907 --> 00:20:06.306
Me too.

157
00:20:06.467 --> 00:20:08.298
- Not me.
- No?

158
00:20:08.467 --> 00:20:12.460
I'm being blackmailed.
but I did what I'm being blackmailed for.

159
00:20:12.627 --> 00:20:14.219
What did you do?

160
00:20:14.387 --> 00:20:20.701
I run a service providing gentlemen
with the company of a young lady.

161
00:20:20.867 --> 00:20:22.937
Oh. yeah?

162
00:20:23.107 --> 00:20:25.098
What's the phone number?

163
00:20:25.267 --> 00:20:28.418
You knew the Colonel works
in Washington. Is he a client?

164
00:20:28.587 --> 00:20:30.578
- No!
- I asked miss Scarlet.

165
00:20:30.747 --> 00:20:32.783
- Say it's not true.
- It's not.

166
00:20:32.947 --> 00:20:34.346
- True?
- No.

167
00:20:34.507 --> 00:20:36.418
- It is true!
- A double negative!

168
00:20:36.587 --> 00:20:39.545
- You have photos?
- Sounds like a confession.

169
00:20:39.707 --> 00:20:42.619
The double negative
has led to proof positive.

170
00:20:42.787 --> 00:20:45.221
Trying to make me look stupid?

171
00:20:45.387 --> 00:20:48.185
- You don't need any help from me.
- Right!

172
00:20:48.347 --> 00:20:52.943
What's so terrible about the Colonel
visiting a house of ill fame?

173
00:20:53.107 --> 00:20:55.177
- Most soldiers do.
- Please!

174
00:20:55.347 --> 00:20:58.066
He holds a sensitive post
in the Pentagon.

175
00:20:58.227 --> 00:21:01.936
You drive a very expensive car
for a colonel.

176
00:21:02.107 --> 00:21:06.578
I came into money during the war
when I lost my parents.

177
00:21:07.947 --> 00:21:10.415
Mrs White. you've been paying

178
00:21:10.587 --> 00:21:13.784
since your husband died
under mysterious circumstances.

179
00:21:15.747 --> 00:21:20.218
- Why is that funny?
- That's why he's on his back. In a coffin.

180
00:21:20.387 --> 00:21:23.538
- I didn't kill him.
- So why pay the blackmailer?

181
00:21:23.707 --> 00:21:28.735
I don't want a scandal. We'd had
a very humiliating confrontation.

182
00:21:28.907 --> 00:21:31.375
He was deranged. He was lunatic.

183
00:21:31.547 --> 00:21:35.460
He didn't like me.
He threatened to kill me in public.

184
00:21:35.627 --> 00:21:40.018
- Why kill you in public?
- He threatened. in public. to kill her.

185
00:21:40.187 --> 00:21:43.896
- Was that his final word?
- Being killed is pretty final.

186
00:21:44.067 --> 00:21:49.983
- Yet he was the one who died. not you.
- What did he do for a living?

187
00:21:50.147 --> 00:21:52.786
A scientist. Nuclear physics.

188
00:21:52.947 --> 00:21:55.017
What was he like?

189
00:21:55.187 --> 00:21:59.544
A stupidly optimistic man.
It came as a shock to him when he died.

190
00:21:59.707 --> 00:22:04.462
He was found at home.
his head had been cut off and his...

191
00:22:04.627 --> 00:22:06.185
You know...

192
00:22:06.347 --> 00:22:09.578
- I'd been at the movies.
- Miss him?

193
00:22:09.747 --> 00:22:13.342
It's life after death.
Now he's dead. I have a life.

194
00:22:13.507 --> 00:22:19.104
- Your first husband also disappeared.
- That was his job. An illusionist.

195
00:22:19.307 --> 00:22:23.664
- But he never reappeared.
- He wasn't a very good illusionist.

196
00:22:24.907 --> 00:22:26.977
I have something to say.

197
00:22:27.147 --> 00:22:31.186
I'm not going to wait
for Wadsworth to unmask me.

198
00:22:31.347 --> 00:22:35.738
I work for the state department.
And I'm a homosexual.

199
00:22:37.387 --> 00:22:40.777
I feel no personal shame
or guilt about this.

200
00:22:40.947 --> 00:22:46.385
But I must keep it a secret
or I'll lose my job on security grounds.

201
00:22:47.547 --> 00:22:49.538
Thank you.

202
00:22:52.347 --> 00:22:54.144
Well...

203
00:22:55.067 --> 00:22:58.742
- That just leaves Mr Boddy.
- What's your little secret?

204
00:22:58.907 --> 00:23:02.536
His secret? Hadn't you guessed?
He's your blackmailer.

205
00:23:04.027 --> 00:23:06.302
- You bastard!
- Colonel!

206
00:23:06.467 --> 00:23:07.900
Put 'em up!

207
00:23:09.827 --> 00:23:14.378
- Gentlemen!
- If you can't fight fairly. don't fight.

208
00:23:14.547 --> 00:23:16.538
He called me a bastard!

209
00:23:18.027 --> 00:23:22.384
- Was that necessary. Mrs White?
- Wait! The police are coming.

210
00:23:22.547 --> 00:23:25.664
- Oh. no!
- My career is very sensitive...

211
00:23:25.827 --> 00:23:28.705
Listen! Blackmail depends on secrecy.

212
00:23:28.867 --> 00:23:31.176
You admit he's blackmailing you.

213
00:23:31.347 --> 00:23:34.623
Tell the police. convict him.
and it will be over.

214
00:23:34.787 --> 00:23:38.905
It's not so easy.
You'll never tell the police.

215
00:23:39.067 --> 00:23:43.583
I shall. I have evidence.
and this conversation is being recorded.

216
00:23:43.747 --> 00:23:47.660
<i>- Recordings aren't admissible evidence.</i>
<i>- Ladies and gentlemen!</i>

217
00:23:47.827 --> 00:23:52.218
The police will be here
in about 45 minutes.

218
00:23:52.387 --> 00:23:56.505
Tell them the truth
and Mr Boddy will be behind bars.

219
00:23:56.667 --> 00:23:59.977
- Where are you going?
- I can help them decide.

220
00:24:00.147 --> 00:24:01.819
I'll get my bag.

221
00:24:11.907 --> 00:24:17.027
- Who can guess what's in here?
- The evidence against us. no doubt.

222
00:24:17.187 --> 00:24:20.224
- Did you know you'd see us tonight?
- Yes.

223
00:24:20.387 --> 00:24:26.383
- What were you told?
- That you'd be discussing our little deal.

224
00:24:26.547 --> 00:24:30.699
And if I didn't appear.
Wadsworth would tell the police about it.

225
00:24:30.867 --> 00:24:35.179
Naturally. I could hardly resist
putting in an appearance.

226
00:24:35.347 --> 00:24:36.985
Excuse me.

227
00:24:38.547 --> 00:24:42.335
- Open 'em.
- Why not?

228
00:24:44.387 --> 00:24:47.697
I enjoy getting presents
from strange men.

229
00:24:56.307 --> 00:24:59.617
A candlestick? What's this for?

230
00:25:43.547 --> 00:25:47.096
In your hands.
you each have a lethal weapon.

231
00:25:50.507 --> 00:25:56.218
If you denounce me to the police.
you will also be exposed and humiliated.

232
00:25:56.387 --> 00:25:58.947
I'll see to that in court.

233
00:26:00.107 --> 00:26:04.623
But... if one of you kills Wadsworth now.

234
00:26:04.787 --> 00:26:08.496
no one but the seven of us
will ever know.

235
00:26:08.667 --> 00:26:12.023
He has the key to the front door...

236
00:26:13.027 --> 00:26:17.578
...which he said would only be opened
over his dead body.

237
00:26:20.027 --> 00:26:23.019
I suggest we take him up on that offer.

238
00:26:28.987 --> 00:26:34.061
The only way to stay off the front pages
is for one of you to kill Wadsworth...

239
00:26:34.227 --> 00:26:35.785
Now!

240
00:26:46.987 --> 00:26:49.501
- It's not Wadsworth!
- Is he alive?

241
00:26:49.667 --> 00:26:53.660
Stand back! Give him air. Let me see...

242
00:26:59.507 --> 00:27:01.418
He's dead.

243
00:27:01.587 --> 00:27:04.420
- Who had the gun?
- Me. but I didn't shoot.

244
00:27:04.587 --> 00:27:07.624
You had the gun.
If you didn't. who did?

245
00:27:09.027 --> 00:27:13.464
Nobody! No gunshot wound! Somebody
grabbed the gun and it went off.

246
00:27:13.627 --> 00:27:17.222
Look. the bullet broke that vase
on the mantle.

247
00:27:17.387 --> 00:27:19.378
- Sorry.
- Excuse me.

248
00:27:19.547 --> 00:27:22.823
He's right.
There's a bullet hole in the wall.

249
00:27:22.987 --> 00:27:27.185
- How did he die?
- I don't know. I'm not a forensic expert.

250
00:27:27.347 --> 00:27:30.657
- One of us must have killed him.
- I didn't.

251
00:27:30.827 --> 00:27:33.216
I need a drink!

252
00:27:36.747 --> 00:27:38.863
Maybe he was poisoned!

253
00:27:40.547 --> 00:27:43.937
Mrs Peacock. please. It's all right.

254
00:27:44.107 --> 00:27:48.703
We don't know anything.
Sit down. Sit down. Mrs...

255
00:27:50.787 --> 00:27:53.824
I... had to stop her from screaming.

256
00:27:53.987 --> 00:27:57.821
- But was the brandy poisoned?
- I don't...

257
00:28:00.867 --> 00:28:05.657
- Looks like we'll never know.
- Unless... unless she dies too.

258
00:28:21.867 --> 00:28:23.858
- It's locked.
- Open up!

259
00:28:24.027 --> 00:28:26.018
- The murderer!
- Screaming?

260
00:28:26.227 --> 00:28:29.185
- It must be Yvette.
- Oh. my God!

261
00:28:32.587 --> 00:28:34.703
- You're alive!
- No thanks to you.

262
00:28:34.867 --> 00:28:39.179
- You locked me up with a murderer!
- The murderer is in this room?

263
00:28:39.347 --> 00:28:43.386
- Where?
- Where? Here!

264
00:28:43.547 --> 00:28:48.541
We are looking at him. or her. As
Mrs White said. one of you is the killer.

265
00:28:48.707 --> 00:28:51.062
- How do you know?
- I was listening.

266
00:28:51.227 --> 00:28:55.539
- But why were you screaming in here?
- I am frightened.

267
00:28:55.707 --> 00:29:01.737
I also drink the cognac. <i>Mon dieu.</i>
I can't stay in here by myself.

268
00:29:03.547 --> 00:29:06.141
- Come with us.
- With the murderer?

269
00:29:06.307 --> 00:29:09.344
There is safety in numbers. my dear.

270
00:29:23.227 --> 00:29:25.263
- No clue how he died?
- No.

271
00:29:25.427 --> 00:29:30.785
This is absolutely terrible.
It's not what I intended. Oh. my God!

272
00:29:30.947 --> 00:29:34.496
- Not what you intended?
- You're not the butler?

273
00:29:34.667 --> 00:29:38.706
Not the butler. but a butler.
In fact. I was his butler.

274
00:29:38.867 --> 00:29:41.700
If he invited us. why was he late?

275
00:29:41.867 --> 00:29:45.780
I invited you. I wrote the letters.
It was all my idea.

276
00:29:45.947 --> 00:29:49.462
Wait a minute. I don't understand.

277
00:29:49.627 --> 00:29:53.097
Why invite us?
Were you helping him blackmail us?

278
00:29:53.267 --> 00:29:56.623
- Certainly not!
- You had better explain.

279
00:29:57.267 --> 00:29:59.781
Please sit down. everyone.

280
00:30:18.627 --> 00:30:22.620
When I said I was Mr Boddy's butler.
it was true but misleading.

281
00:30:22.787 --> 00:30:27.941
I was once his butler. But it was not
his death that ended my employment.

282
00:30:28.107 --> 00:30:32.578
- When did it end?
- When my wife decided to end her life.

283
00:30:32.747 --> 00:30:37.059
She too was being blackmailed
by this odious man who lies dead.

284
00:30:37.227 --> 00:30:40.742
He hated my wife
for the same reason he hated you.

285
00:30:40.907 --> 00:30:43.979
He believed you were all
thoroughly UN-American.

286
00:30:48.147 --> 00:30:50.945
- Sorry.
- He felt it was inappropriate

287
00:30:51.107 --> 00:30:56.135
for a senator to have a corrupt wife.
a doctor to take advantage of patients.

288
00:30:56.307 --> 00:31:00.744
for a wife to emasculate
her husband and... so forth...

289
00:31:00.907 --> 00:31:04.820
It's ridiculous. Why didn't he
report us to the authorities?

290
00:31:04.987 --> 00:31:10.823
He decided to use his information
to make some money - very American!

291
00:31:10.987 --> 00:31:15.503
- What was your role?
- I was a victim. too.

292
00:31:15.667 --> 00:31:20.502
At least. my wife was.
She had friends who were...

293
00:31:21.867 --> 00:31:25.303
- Socialists!
- Oh. my God!

294
00:31:28.547 --> 00:31:31.903
Well. we all make mistakes.

295
00:31:42.467 --> 00:31:46.506
He threatened to report her
unless she named her friends.

296
00:31:46.667 --> 00:31:50.342
She refused. so he blackmailed her.
We had no money.

297
00:31:50.507 --> 00:31:54.659
The price of his silence
was that we work for nothing. like slaves.

298
00:31:54.827 --> 00:31:57.978
- To make a long story short...
- Too late!

299
00:31:58.147 --> 00:32:02.345
The suicide of my wife
created a sense of injustice in me.

300
00:32:02.507 --> 00:32:04.737
I resolved to put Mr Boddy in jail.

301
00:32:04.907 --> 00:32:09.458
It seemed the best way to do it.
and free you from blackmail too.

302
00:32:09.627 --> 00:32:14.018
was to get everyone face to face.
confront Mr Boddy with his crimes.

303
00:32:14.187 --> 00:32:16.747
and turn him over to the police.

304
00:32:16.907 --> 00:32:22.265
- So. everything is explained.
- We still don't know who killed him.

305
00:32:22.427 --> 00:32:25.703
We have to find out
before the police arrive.

306
00:32:25.867 --> 00:32:30.622
- We can't have the police now!
- How can we know which of you did it?

307
00:32:30.787 --> 00:32:33.301
- Why "which of you"?
- I didn't.

308
00:32:33.467 --> 00:32:36.300
All of us had the opportunity
and a motive.

309
00:32:36.467 --> 00:32:38.856
- Great!
- Maybe it wasn't one of us.

310
00:32:39.027 --> 00:32:41.063
- Who else?
- Who else is here?

311
00:32:41.227 --> 00:32:43.024
- The cook...
- The cook!

312
00:33:11.947 --> 00:33:14.905
Well. she's not here.

313
00:33:18.467 --> 00:33:20.458
I didn't do it!

314
00:33:20.627 --> 00:33:25.018
Would somebody help me. please?
Help me. please!

315
00:33:31.667 --> 00:33:36.866
- Don't touch it. it's evidence.
- We have to find out who did this.

316
00:33:37.027 --> 00:33:40.178
- You'd better explain yourself.
- Me? Why?

317
00:33:40.347 --> 00:33:42.736
- Why kill the cook?
- Dinner was OK.

318
00:33:42.907 --> 00:33:46.741
- How can you make jokes?
- It's my defence mechanism.

319
00:33:46.907 --> 00:33:51.503
Some defence!
If I was the killer. I'd kill you next.

320
00:33:51.667 --> 00:33:54.181
I said "if"...!

321
00:33:55.867 --> 00:34:00.816
- The only admitted killer here is her.
- I've admitted nothing.

322
00:34:00.987 --> 00:34:03.979
- How many husbands have you had?
- Mine?

323
00:34:04.147 --> 00:34:06.377
- Yours.
- Five. just five.

324
00:34:06.547 --> 00:34:09.664
Husbands are like Kleenex.
soft. strong. disposable.

325
00:34:09.827 --> 00:34:12.625
You lure them like a spider with flies.

326
00:34:12.787 --> 00:34:16.575
- Flies are where men are vulnerable.
- Right.

327
00:34:16.747 --> 00:34:21.457
If it wasn't you. who was it?
Who had the dagger? Mrs Peacock!

328
00:34:21.627 --> 00:34:24.300
- I put it down. in the study.
- When?

329
00:34:24.467 --> 00:34:28.824
I don't know...
Before I fainted. after I fainted.

330
00:34:28.987 --> 00:34:32.423
But any of you could have picked it up.

331
00:34:32.587 --> 00:34:36.057
I suggest we take the cook's body
into the study.

332
00:34:36.227 --> 00:34:39.697
- Why?
- I'm the butler. I keep the kitchen tidy.

333
00:34:46.507 --> 00:34:49.101
Look! The body's gone!

334
00:34:49.267 --> 00:34:52.703
- What are you staring at? Who's there?
- Nobody.

335
00:34:52.867 --> 00:34:56.746
- What do you mean?
- No body. Mr Boddy's body has gone.

336
00:34:56.907 --> 00:34:59.546
Maybe he wasn't dead.
We should have made sure.

337
00:34:59.707 --> 00:35:02.096
- By cutting his head off?
- Really!

338
00:35:02.267 --> 00:35:05.179
- Where is he?
- We'd better look for him.

339
00:35:16.347 --> 00:35:18.338
Well...

340
00:35:19.347 --> 00:35:24.102
- He couldn't have been dead.
- He was! At least. I thought he was.

341
00:35:24.267 --> 00:35:28.658
- What's the difference?
- Quite a difference to him.

342
00:35:28.827 --> 00:35:34.299
- Maybe there is life after death.
- As improbable as sex after marriage.

343
00:35:34.467 --> 00:35:38.301
- Maybe Mr Boddy killed the cook!
- Yes!

344
00:35:38.467 --> 00:35:40.458
How?

345
00:35:46.147 --> 00:35:51.016
If you'll excuse me...
Is there a little girl's room?

346
00:35:51.187 --> 00:35:56.181
- <i>Oui. oui. madame.</i>
- No. I just want to powder my nose.

347
00:35:57.347 --> 00:35:59.065
What's this?

348
00:35:59.227 --> 00:36:02.856
- The negatives the Colonel referred to.
- My God!

349
00:36:03.027 --> 00:36:05.860
- Planning to blackmail him?
- Certainly not!

350
00:36:06.027 --> 00:36:10.384
I was going to give them to the Colonel
once Mr Boddy was unmasked.

351
00:36:10.547 --> 00:36:13.744
Very pretty! Want to see?
They might shock you.

352
00:36:13.907 --> 00:36:17.695
- No. I am a lady.
- So how d'you know what they're like?

353
00:36:17.867 --> 00:36:20.461
- What are they like?
- I'd like them back.

354
00:36:20.627 --> 00:36:24.336
- Something in them concerns me. too.
- Let me see.

355
00:36:24.507 --> 00:36:30.025
- My! Nobody can get into that position.
- Sure they can. Let me show you.

356
00:36:30.707 --> 00:36:32.026
Get off!

357
00:36:40.747 --> 00:36:43.307
Mr Boddy! He's attacking her.

358
00:36:47.587 --> 00:36:51.739
- No. he's dead.
- Mr Boddy. dead? Again?!

359
00:36:51.907 --> 00:36:54.182
- Oh. my God!
- She's fainting.

360
00:36:54.347 --> 00:36:57.623
- Catch her!
- I'll catch her. Fall into my arms.

361
00:36:59.827 --> 00:37:03.786
- Sorry.
- You've got blood on your hands.

362
00:37:03.947 --> 00:37:06.063
I didn't do it!

363
00:37:06.747 --> 00:37:08.738
He's got new injuries.

364
00:37:08.907 --> 00:37:11.580
He's dead now.
Why kill him twice?

365
00:37:11.747 --> 00:37:14.307
- Unnecessary.
- What we call "overkill".

366
00:37:14.467 --> 00:37:17.027
- Psychotic.
- Unless he wasn't dead.

367
00:37:17.187 --> 00:37:20.179
- So what?
- That's what we want to find out!

368
00:37:20.347 --> 00:37:24.340
- Who killed him. where. and with what.
- No need to shout.

369
00:37:24.507 --> 00:37:27.499
I'm not shouting!

370
00:37:27.667 --> 00:37:30.625
All right. I am.
I'm shouting. I'm shouting...

371
00:37:43.067 --> 00:37:45.706
OK. put the corpses on the sofa.

372
00:37:46.867 --> 00:37:48.937
Ladies first.

373
00:38:00.027 --> 00:38:04.703
- Don't get blood on the sofa.
- The dagger will go further into her back.

374
00:38:04.867 --> 00:38:07.586
Tip her forward. over the arm.

375
00:38:11.507 --> 00:38:13.498
Now Mr Boddy.

376
00:38:14.947 --> 00:38:16.938
Ready...

377
00:38:19.187 --> 00:38:22.065
- A little higher.
- There you go.

378
00:38:25.707 --> 00:38:27.698
Now... who...

379
00:38:29.827 --> 00:38:33.137
- Who had the candlestick?
- It was given to you.

380
00:38:33.307 --> 00:38:35.980
I dropped it.
Anyone could've picked it up.

381
00:38:36.147 --> 00:38:41.904
We have all these weapons. the gun.
the rope. the wrench. the lead pipe.

382
00:38:42.067 --> 00:38:47.141
Let's lock them all in this cupboard.
There's a homicidal maniac about.

383
00:38:47.307 --> 00:38:49.537
- That's wise.
- Good idea.

384
00:38:49.707 --> 00:38:53.177
- Why are you pocketing the key?
- To keep it safe.

385
00:38:53.347 --> 00:38:57.579
That means you can open it.
What if you're the murderer?

386
00:38:57.747 --> 00:38:59.738
- I'm not.
- What if you are?

387
00:38:59.907 --> 00:39:02.137
It has to go somewhere.
I know I'm safe.

388
00:39:02.307 --> 00:39:04.298
We don't!

389
00:39:04.467 --> 00:39:07.539
- I have an idea. We'll throw it away.
- Good idea.

390
00:39:07.707 --> 00:39:09.698
- Brilliant.
- That'll do it.

391
00:39:14.227 --> 00:39:16.218
Sorry...

392
00:39:17.027 --> 00:39:19.700
Sorry... can we help?

393
00:39:19.867 --> 00:39:23.098
I didn't mean to disturb
the whole household.

394
00:39:23.267 --> 00:39:28.899
My car broke down and I was wondering
if I could use your phone.

395
00:39:29.067 --> 00:39:31.058
Just a moment.

396
00:39:43.627 --> 00:39:46.937
Very well. sir.
Would you care to come in?

397
00:39:47.867 --> 00:39:50.301
- Well. where is it?
- The body?

398
00:39:50.467 --> 00:39:54.096
- The phone. What body?
- No body. Nobody in the study.

399
00:39:54.267 --> 00:39:57.225
- No!
- But there's a phone in the lounge.

400
00:39:57.387 --> 00:39:59.184
Thank you.

401
00:40:05.427 --> 00:40:10.182
- When you've finished. please wait here.
- Certainly.

402
00:40:24.267 --> 00:40:28.146
- Where's the key?
- The key to the weapons cupboard.

403
00:40:28.307 --> 00:40:31.219
- You still wish me to throw it away?
- Yes!

404
00:40:42.867 --> 00:40:45.745
Well... what now?

405
00:40:45.907 --> 00:40:50.185
- Wadsworth. let me out.
- No. we've got to know who did it.

406
00:40:50.347 --> 00:40:54.022
- If you go. I'll say you killed them both.
- Me too.

407
00:40:54.187 --> 00:40:58.738
I'll make you sorry you started this.
one day when we're alone.

408
00:40:58.907 --> 00:41:01.740
No sane man
would be alone with you.

409
00:41:01.907 --> 00:41:05.217
- I could use a drink.
- So could I.

410
00:41:06.267 --> 00:41:10.055
Just checking...
Two corpses. everything's fine.

411
00:41:13.507 --> 00:41:16.499
- Anybody else want a whisky?
- Yeah.

412
00:41:17.747 --> 00:41:21.899
All right. look. Pay attention. everybody.

413
00:41:22.067 --> 00:41:25.025
Am I right that there is nobody else here?

414
00:41:25.187 --> 00:41:27.223
- No.
- There is someone else.

415
00:41:27.387 --> 00:41:30.743
- No. I said no meaning yes.
- No meaning yes?

416
00:41:30.907 --> 00:41:35.264
I want a straight answer.
Is there someone else? Yes or no?

417
00:41:35.427 --> 00:41:38.658
- No.
- "No. there is". or "No. there isn't"?

418
00:41:38.827 --> 00:41:40.624
- Yes.
- Please!

419
00:41:42.547 --> 00:41:47.063
Shouldn't we get rid of that man
before he finds out what's going on?

420
00:41:47.227 --> 00:41:51.584
- We can't throw him out.
- If he stays. he'll get suspicious.

421
00:41:51.747 --> 00:41:55.183
- If he goes. he'll be suspicious.
- I'd be suspicious.

422
00:41:55.347 --> 00:42:00.740
Who cares? Let him stay locked up
for another half an hour.

423
00:42:00.907 --> 00:42:06.664
The police will be here by then. and
there are two dead bodies in the study!

424
00:42:08.267 --> 00:42:11.623
There's confusion as to whether
there's anyone else here.

425
00:42:11.787 --> 00:42:14.540
- There isn't.
- Confusion or anybody else?

426
00:42:14.707 --> 00:42:17.141
- Either. Or both.
- Gimme a clear answer.

427
00:42:17.307 --> 00:42:20.424
- Certainly. The question?
- Is anybody else here?

428
00:42:20.587 --> 00:42:25.377
- No!
- So he says. But does he know?

429
00:42:25.547 --> 00:42:30.940
I suggest we do this in military fashion.
We split up and search the house.

430
00:42:31.107 --> 00:42:33.098
- Split up?!
- Yes.

431
00:42:33.267 --> 00:42:36.703
We have very little time.
so we'll split into pairs.

432
00:42:36.867 --> 00:42:39.097
What if one of us is the murderer?

433
00:42:39.267 --> 00:42:42.464
Whoever is left with the killer
might get killed.

434
00:42:42.627 --> 00:42:47.303
- Then we'll discover the murderer.
- But one of the pair will be dead!

435
00:42:47.467 --> 00:42:50.664
This is war. Peacock!
Casualties are inevitable.

436
00:42:50.827 --> 00:42:53.899
Making omelettes means breaking eggs.
every cook knows.

437
00:42:54.067 --> 00:42:57.184
Look what happened to the cook!

438
00:42:57.347 --> 00:43:00.737
- Will you take that chance?
- What choice have we?

439
00:43:00.907 --> 00:43:03.137
- None.
- You're right.

440
00:43:03.307 --> 00:43:09.064
<i>Bon. d'accord.</i> But it is dark upstairs.
Will anyone go with me?

441
00:43:09.227 --> 00:43:11.866
- I will.
- No. thank you.

442
00:43:12.027 --> 00:43:16.623
I suggest we all draw lots. for partners.

443
00:43:36.027 --> 00:43:41.021
Ready? The two shortest together.
the next two shortest together. Agreed?

444
00:43:41.187 --> 00:43:45.897
I suggest the two shortest
search the cellar and so on. up.

445
00:44:29.787 --> 00:44:32.620
It's you and me. honey-bunch.

446
00:44:47.427 --> 00:44:50.021
The cellar.

447
00:44:51.187 --> 00:44:54.543
We know what's in the study
and the library.

448
00:44:54.707 --> 00:44:59.019
- The stranger's in the lounge.
- Let's go with the billiard-room.

449
00:45:32.347 --> 00:45:35.259
- Want to go in front?
- Absolutely no.

450
00:45:35.427 --> 00:45:38.544
- I'm sure there's no one there.
- Then you go.

451
00:45:38.707 --> 00:45:40.743
All right.

452
00:46:01.827 --> 00:46:06.742
- Well. ladies first.
- No. you can go first.

453
00:46:06.907 --> 00:46:08.784
- I insist.
- I insist.

454
00:46:08.947 --> 00:46:12.337
- Afraid of a fate worse than death?
- Just death.

455
00:46:15.147 --> 00:46:17.786
- Are you going in there?
- Yes.

456
00:46:19.707 --> 00:46:21.698
- Right.
- Right.

457
00:46:25.307 --> 00:46:29.061
- I see no light switches.
- Nor do I. There must be some.

458
00:46:29.227 --> 00:46:31.218
- Shall I come with you?
- No!

459
00:46:31.387 --> 00:46:34.185
I mean... no. thank you.

460
00:46:44.587 --> 00:46:46.976
- Ladies first.
- No. thanks.

461
00:47:22.707 --> 00:47:26.586
- Go on. I'll be right behind you.
- That's why I'm nervous.

462
00:47:26.747 --> 00:47:29.386
Then we go together.

463
00:47:47.627 --> 00:47:49.857
Stay there!

464
00:47:56.707 --> 00:48:00.666
If there's anybody in here. just look out!

465
00:48:00.827 --> 00:48:04.581
Are you hiding? I'm coming!

466
00:48:07.467 --> 00:48:09.776
- What room's this?
- Search me.

467
00:48:09.947 --> 00:48:14.145
- All right.
- Get your mitts off me.

468
00:48:35.347 --> 00:48:39.022
- Nobody here.
- He's behind one of those curtains.

469
00:48:40.107 --> 00:48:43.622
You look. I'll search the kitchen.

470
00:50:13.787 --> 00:50:15.778
I'm a little nervous.

471
00:50:16.867 --> 00:50:22.066
I'm in this big house.
and I've been locked into the lounge.

472
00:50:22.227 --> 00:50:24.218
Yes...

473
00:50:24.387 --> 00:50:30.826
The funny thing is. there's a group
of people here having a sort of party.

474
00:50:30.987 --> 00:50:34.457
And one of them is my old boss from...

475
00:51:18.307 --> 00:51:21.105
Looks like a secret passage.

476
00:51:23.107 --> 00:51:27.100
- Shall we see where it leads?
- What the hell?

477
00:51:27.267 --> 00:51:29.735
I'll go first. I've had a good life.

478
00:51:33.747 --> 00:51:35.977
- Oh. God!
- It's all right.

479
00:51:47.267 --> 00:51:49.064
Oh. my God!

480
00:51:57.507 --> 00:52:00.260
Come on! We're locked in here!

481
00:52:03.907 --> 00:52:05.863
Help!

482
00:52:06.867 --> 00:52:11.577
Down here! Get us out of here!

483
00:52:11.747 --> 00:52:14.500
- Where's it coming from?
- Where are we going?

484
00:52:14.667 --> 00:52:17.625
- Where are they?
- The lounge.

485
00:52:18.707 --> 00:52:20.698
We're in here!

486
00:52:20.867 --> 00:52:22.858
- The door's locked!
- I know!

487
00:52:23.027 --> 00:52:25.143
- Where's the key?
- It's gone!

488
00:52:25.307 --> 00:52:30.381
- Never mind. unlock the door!
- I can't unlock it without the key!

489
00:52:30.547 --> 00:52:33.220
- Let us in!
- Let us out!

490
00:52:33.387 --> 00:52:35.901
It's no good. Stand back.

491
00:52:36.067 --> 00:52:40.060
There's no alternative.
I'll just have to break it down.

492
00:52:42.267 --> 00:52:45.464
- I know. I have it!
- Help!

493
00:52:45.627 --> 00:52:49.415
Will you shut up? We're doing our best!

494
00:52:52.947 --> 00:52:54.938
They're shooting at us.

495
00:53:02.787 --> 00:53:07.178
- I've been shot!
- Come out! The door is open!

496
00:53:09.067 --> 00:53:13.185
- Why are you shooting at us?
- To get you out.

497
00:53:13.347 --> 00:53:16.737
You could have killed us.
I could've been killed.

498
00:53:16.907 --> 00:53:20.058
I can't take any more scares.

499
00:53:25.627 --> 00:53:27.663
Look!

500
00:53:29.707 --> 00:53:33.416
- Which one of you did it?
- We found him. together.

501
00:53:33.587 --> 00:53:38.103
- How did you get in?
- There's a secret passage.

502
00:53:38.267 --> 00:53:41.418
Is that the same gun?
The cupboard was locked!

503
00:53:41.587 --> 00:53:43.464
- Unlocked.
- Unlocked?

504
00:53:43.627 --> 00:53:45.982
See for yourself.

505
00:53:53.787 --> 00:53:56.540
How did you know
you could get at the gun?

506
00:53:56.707 --> 00:54:00.620
I didn't. I think I break it open.
but it was open already.

507
00:54:00.787 --> 00:54:03.096
A likely story.

508
00:54:05.587 --> 00:54:08.260
Maybe they'll just go away.

509
00:54:17.827 --> 00:54:19.818
- I'm going to open it.
- Why?

510
00:54:19.987 --> 00:54:24.697
I have nothing to hide. I didn't do it!
The key.

511
00:54:25.707 --> 00:54:27.106
Thank you.

512
00:54:29.827 --> 00:54:31.977
Good evening. sir.

513
00:54:33.827 --> 00:54:37.661
- Yes?
- I found an abandoned car at the gate.

514
00:54:37.827 --> 00:54:42.776
- Did the driver come in here for help?
- No.

515
00:54:42.947 --> 00:54:45.461
- Well. actually. yes.
- No!

516
00:54:45.627 --> 00:54:50.143
- Seems to be some disagreement.
- No!

517
00:54:50.307 --> 00:54:51.899
Yes.

518
00:54:52.067 --> 00:54:56.299
- Can I come in and use your phone?
- Of course. sir.

519
00:54:56.467 --> 00:54:59.379
You may use the one in the... no...

520
00:54:59.547 --> 00:55:02.823
You could use the one in the St... No...

521
00:55:02.987 --> 00:55:07.344
Would you be kind enough
to wait in... in the library?

522
00:55:07.507 --> 00:55:09.498
Sure.

523
00:55:14.667 --> 00:55:17.659
Don't I know you from someplace?

524
00:55:18.667 --> 00:55:20.862
You all seem very anxious.

525
00:55:21.027 --> 00:55:25.703
The chandelier fell and almost killed us.
Would you come this way?

526
00:55:34.027 --> 00:55:37.337
Frightfully draughty. these old houses.

527
00:55:39.507 --> 00:55:42.704
Please help yourself to a drink.
if you'd like.

528
00:55:42.867 --> 00:55:46.655
- Not the cognac. just in case.
- In case of what?

529
00:55:51.547 --> 00:55:53.538
What now?

530
00:55:56.027 --> 00:55:58.302
- We should've told.
- You say that now.

531
00:55:58.467 --> 00:56:01.186
- I said it then.
- Oh. shut up!

532
00:56:01.347 --> 00:56:03.736
Let's clean this up.

533
00:56:14.667 --> 00:56:16.862
Hello?

534
00:56:17.307 --> 00:56:21.858
- Maybe the cop answered it.
- And who shall I say is calling?

535
00:56:23.987 --> 00:56:26.706
Would you hold on. please?

536
00:56:30.067 --> 00:56:34.504
Let me outta here!
You have no right to shut me in.

537
00:56:34.667 --> 00:56:38.342
I'll book you for false arrest.
wrongful imprisonment.

538
00:56:38.507 --> 00:56:43.376
and obstructing an officer
in the course of his duty and murder.

539
00:56:44.507 --> 00:56:46.941
What do you mean. "murder"?

540
00:56:47.107 --> 00:56:51.180
I just said it so you'd open the door.
What's going on?

541
00:56:51.347 --> 00:56:56.296
Why lock me in? Why are you
getting calls from J Edgar Hoover?

542
00:56:56.467 --> 00:57:01.541
- J Edgar Hoover?
- That's right. The head of the FBI!

543
00:57:01.707 --> 00:57:06.178
- Why is he on your phone?
- He's on everyone's. Why not mine?

544
00:57:06.347 --> 00:57:08.338
Excuse me.

545
00:57:13.707 --> 00:57:17.666
- What's going on here?
- We're having a party.

546
00:57:18.907 --> 00:57:22.104
- Mind if I look around?
- Sure!

547
00:57:24.507 --> 00:57:27.146
- You can show him around. Mr Green.
- Me?

548
00:57:27.307 --> 00:57:33.257
Yes. you can show him the dining-room.
the kitchen. the ballroom...

549
00:57:33.427 --> 00:57:35.418
Fine!

550
00:57:35.587 --> 00:57:39.341
Fine. Officer. come with me.

551
00:57:39.507 --> 00:57:44.137
I'll show you the dining-room
or the kitchen or the ballroom...

552
00:57:47.747 --> 00:57:49.817
Make it look convincing.

553
00:57:51.587 --> 00:57:54.465
- So. this is the dining-room.
- No kidding!

554
00:57:54.627 --> 00:57:56.140
Come on!

555
00:57:56.307 --> 00:58:00.425
- What's going on in those two rooms?
- Which two rooms?

556
00:58:05.467 --> 00:58:08.220
- Those two rooms.
- Oh. those two rooms!

557
00:58:08.387 --> 00:58:10.378
Yes.

558
00:58:11.787 --> 00:58:16.099
- Officer. you shouldn't go in there.
- Why not?

559
00:58:17.947 --> 00:58:20.939
Because it's all too shocking.

560
00:58:45.587 --> 00:58:50.502
It's not all that shocking.
These folks are just having a good time.

561
00:58:59.027 --> 00:59:00.426
My God!

562
00:59:05.387 --> 00:59:07.378
Excuse me.

563
00:59:17.907 --> 00:59:21.786
- This man's drunk. Dead drunk.
- Dead right!

564
00:59:23.387 --> 00:59:27.858
- You're not going to drive home?
- He won't drive. I promise you.

565
00:59:28.027 --> 00:59:30.746
- He'll get a lift?
- We'll get him a car.

566
00:59:30.907 --> 00:59:33.705
- A long black car.
- A limousine.

567
00:59:44.707 --> 00:59:46.777
- Officer!
- I've seen it all.

568
00:59:46.947 --> 00:59:49.905
- I can explain everything.
- You don't have to.

569
00:59:50.067 --> 00:59:53.423
- Don't worry. it's nothing illegal.
- Are you sure?

570
00:59:53.587 --> 00:59:55.578
- This is America.
- I see.

571
00:59:55.747 --> 01:00:00.263
- It's a free country.
- I didn't know it was that free.

572
01:00:01.827 --> 01:00:05.786
- May I use your phone now?
- Certainly.

573
01:00:13.107 --> 01:00:14.426
Why lock him in?

574
01:00:15.067 --> 01:00:17.979
We haven't finished
searching the house yet!

575
01:00:18.147 --> 01:00:22.265
- Only 15 minutes till the police come.
- They already came!

576
01:00:22.427 --> 01:00:25.180
- Shut up!
- Let's get on with it.

577
01:00:53.867 --> 01:00:57.542
Look! I can't believe it.
I wonder where this one goes?

578
01:00:57.707 --> 01:01:00.096
Let's find out.

579
01:01:18.587 --> 01:01:21.465
Let's try the ballroom again.

580
01:01:46.227 --> 01:01:48.946
Don't you touch me!

581
01:02:01.667 --> 01:02:04.056
Hello?

582
01:02:05.147 --> 01:02:10.141
Shut the door.
Did anyone recognise you?

583
01:02:10.307 --> 01:02:15.506
They must have. And not just my face.
They know every inch of my body.

584
01:02:15.667 --> 01:02:18.135
And they're not the only ones.

585
01:02:18.307 --> 01:02:20.343
It's you!

586
01:02:23.107 --> 01:02:28.545
There's something funny going on
around here. I don't know what it is.

587
01:02:30.067 --> 01:02:35.903
No. I'm not on duty.
But I have a feeling that I'm in danger.

588
01:02:36.067 --> 01:02:38.342
You know that big. ugly house...

589
01:02:38.507 --> 01:02:40.896
Hello?

590
01:02:41.067 --> 01:02:43.183
Hello?

591
01:02:44.547 --> 01:02:46.856
Are you there?

592
01:02:55.747 --> 01:02:58.466
<i>I am</i>
<i>your singing telegram!</i>

593
01:03:08.147 --> 01:03:11.457
I'm coming!
I'm just trying to find the door.

594
01:03:11.627 --> 01:03:14.778
- Help me. please!
- Coming.

595
01:03:15.947 --> 01:03:18.859
What's this? Another door?

596
01:04:25.987 --> 01:04:28.501
Two murders.

597
01:04:36.027 --> 01:04:39.337
- Neither was shot. I heard a gun.
- So did I.

598
01:04:39.507 --> 01:04:43.625
- I heard the front door slam.
- The murderer must have run out.

599
01:04:48.587 --> 01:04:51.818
- Three murders.
- Six altogether.

600
01:04:52.947 --> 01:04:55.541
This is getting serious.

601
01:05:03.547 --> 01:05:06.300
No gun. Yvette dropped it here.

602
01:05:08.147 --> 01:05:11.503
- Very well. I know who did it.
- You do?

603
01:05:11.667 --> 01:05:15.262
Furthermore. I'm going to tell you
how it was done.

604
01:05:15.427 --> 01:05:17.463
Follow me.

605
01:05:20.147 --> 01:05:25.540
To help you understand. I shall take
you through the events step by step.

606
01:05:25.707 --> 01:05:31.623
At the start. Yvette was here by herself.
waiting to offer you champagne.

607
01:05:31.787 --> 01:05:34.779
I was in the hall.

608
01:05:36.347 --> 01:05:40.420
I know. I was there.
Then I hurried across to the kitchen.

609
01:05:42.827 --> 01:05:46.103
The cook was in here. alive.
sharpening knives.

610
01:05:46.267 --> 01:05:48.622
And then...

611
01:05:49.227 --> 01:05:51.616
The doorbell rang...

612
01:05:52.787 --> 01:05:57.383
It was you. I asked for your coat
and stopped you from saying your name

613
01:05:57.547 --> 01:06:00.698
as I wanted you to use pseudonyms.
I introduced myself as the butler.

614
01:06:00.867 --> 01:06:04.382
and I ran across the hall to the library.

615
01:06:04.547 --> 01:06:09.257
Then Yvette met you. and smiled.
and poured you a drink.

616
01:06:11.307 --> 01:06:15.698
The doorbell rang. It was Mrs White.
I took her coat and hung it up.

617
01:06:17.507 --> 01:06:20.499
I introduced Mrs White
to Colonel Mustard.

618
01:06:20.667 --> 01:06:24.103
and I noticed that Mrs White
and Yvette flinched.

619
01:06:24.267 --> 01:06:28.021
There was a rumble of thunder
and a crash of lightning.

620
01:06:28.187 --> 01:06:29.825
- In short...
- Too late!

621
01:06:29.987 --> 01:06:31.579
You all arrived.

622
01:06:31.747 --> 01:06:37.140
Then the gong was struck by the cook
and we went into the dining-room.

623
01:06:38.587 --> 01:06:41.226
Mrs Peacock sat here.
Professor Plum here.

624
01:06:41.387 --> 01:06:44.220
Mrs White. Mr Green.
miss Scarlet. Colonel Mustard.

625
01:06:44.387 --> 01:06:49.381
This chair was vacant. Anyway.
we all revealed we'd had a letter...

626
01:06:49.547 --> 01:06:52.380
- Get on with it!
- The point is. blackmail.

627
01:06:52.547 --> 01:06:56.256
- All this came out in the study.
- You're right.

628
01:06:59.467 --> 01:07:05.303
Mr green stood here. Mrs Peacock here.
miss Scarlet. Professor Plum. Colonel...

629
01:07:05.467 --> 01:07:07.856
- Get on with it!
- I'm getting there!

630
01:07:08.027 --> 01:07:11.815
Mr Boddy got packages from the hall.
you opened your presents.

631
01:07:11.987 --> 01:07:14.785
Mr Boddy switched out the lights...

632
01:07:20.747 --> 01:07:22.863
- Oh. my God.
- Grand!

633
01:07:23.027 --> 01:07:26.576
- Mr Boddy lay apparently dead.
- He was dead!

634
01:07:26.747 --> 01:07:29.466
So why was he bashed
with a candlestick?

635
01:07:29.627 --> 01:07:31.982
- OK. I made a mistake!
- Right.

636
01:07:32.147 --> 01:07:34.980
But why did Mr Boddy
pretend he was dead?

637
01:07:35.147 --> 01:07:37.820
Because he realised
his scheme had misfired.

638
01:07:37.987 --> 01:07:41.024
The gunshot was intended to kill him.
not me.

639
01:07:41.187 --> 01:07:45.897
The bullet grazed him. He escaped death
by pretending to be dead already.

640
01:07:46.067 --> 01:07:49.104
Whoever grabbed the gun
was trying to kill him!

641
01:07:49.267 --> 01:07:52.100
What happened next?
Mrs Peacock took a drink.

642
01:07:52.267 --> 01:07:55.942
You said. "maybe it's poisoned."
She screams.

643
01:07:56.107 --> 01:07:58.826
We took her to the sofa...

644
01:07:58.987 --> 01:08:01.262
Mr green...

645
01:08:01.427 --> 01:08:04.737
Well. I had to stop her screaming...

646
01:08:04.907 --> 01:08:10.220
Then more screaming. Yvette!
We all rushed to the billiard-room.

647
01:08:10.387 --> 01:08:13.424
- But one of us wasn't here. No.
- No?

648
01:08:13.587 --> 01:08:16.499
No. Maybe one of us
was murdering the cook.

649
01:08:16.667 --> 01:08:19.943
- Who wasn't here with us?
- Do you know?

650
01:08:20.107 --> 01:08:25.101
I do. While we stood here.
trying to stop Yvette from panicking.

651
01:08:25.267 --> 01:08:27.986
one of us
could have taken the dagger.

652
01:08:28.147 --> 01:08:30.707
run down the hall.

653
01:08:30.867 --> 01:08:33.097
and stabbed the cook.

654
01:08:33.267 --> 01:08:38.500
- We'd have seen them run back.
- Not if they used this secret passage.

655
01:08:38.667 --> 01:08:41.977
And the murderer ran
down the passage to the study.

656
01:08:42.147 --> 01:08:45.617
- Is that where it comes out?
- Yes. look.

657
01:08:46.747 --> 01:08:49.978
- How did you know?
- This house belongs to a friend.

658
01:08:50.147 --> 01:08:52.820
- You could be the murderer.
- Ridiculous!

659
01:08:52.987 --> 01:08:56.662
If I was the murderer.
why would I tell you how I did it?

660
01:08:56.827 --> 01:09:00.615
- Who else knew of the passage?
- Me and the Colonel found it.

661
01:09:00.787 --> 01:09:04.780
- You could've known all along.
- Why should we believe you?

662
01:09:04.947 --> 01:09:08.701
She was with us while Yvette
was screaming. remember?

663
01:09:08.867 --> 01:09:13.099
Why was the cook murdered?
She had nothing to do with Mr Boddy.

664
01:09:13.267 --> 01:09:19.536
She did! I gathered you here because
you were all implicated in his blackmail.

665
01:09:19.707 --> 01:09:23.586
Did none of you deduce
that the others were involved. too?

666
01:09:23.747 --> 01:09:25.738
- Who?
- The cook and Yvette.

667
01:09:25.907 --> 01:09:29.456
- No!
- That's how he got his information.

668
01:09:29.627 --> 01:09:33.381
Before blackmailing anyone.
he had to discover their secret.

669
01:09:33.547 --> 01:09:35.777
The cook and Yvette were accomplices.

670
01:09:35.947 --> 01:09:41.704
I see. So. whoever knew
that the cook was involved...

671
01:09:41.867 --> 01:09:44.904
...killed her?
- Yes.

672
01:09:45.067 --> 01:09:49.538
I know. as Mr Boddy's butler.
that the cook worked for one of you.

673
01:09:49.707 --> 01:09:53.222
- Who?
- You recognised Yvette. Don't deny it.

674
01:09:53.387 --> 01:09:57.380
- What do you mean? I deny nothing.
- Another denial.

675
01:09:58.507 --> 01:10:03.627
OK. I knew Yvette. My husband
had an affair with her. I didn't care.

676
01:10:03.787 --> 01:10:06.460
- You knew Yvette.
- She worked for me.

677
01:10:06.627 --> 01:10:11.417
You also knew her.
You were one of miss Scarlet's clients.

678
01:10:11.587 --> 01:10:17.219
That's why you wanted those photos.
You and Yvette <i>in flagrante delicto.</i>

679
01:10:17.387 --> 01:10:22.142
Mr Boddy threatened to send them
to my mother. It would've killed her.

680
01:10:22.307 --> 01:10:27.142
Amazing. since you told us she's
dead already. So. he had the motive.

681
01:10:27.307 --> 01:10:30.743
- You all did.
- Where and when was Mr Boddy killed?

682
01:10:30.907 --> 01:10:36.106
Don't you see? We came back from
the study. Mr Boddy was on the floor.

683
01:10:36.267 --> 01:10:39.384
pretending to be dead.
One of us knows he's alive.

684
01:10:39.547 --> 01:10:44.382
I said I'd invited you and we realised
there was only one other person here.

685
01:10:44.547 --> 01:10:46.902
The cook!

686
01:10:53.507 --> 01:10:55.896
Where is he?

687
01:11:01.387 --> 01:11:05.266
She was dead. We laid her down.
our backs to the freezer.

688
01:11:05.427 --> 01:11:08.658
- One of us went through the passage...
- Again?

689
01:11:08.827 --> 01:11:10.818
...back to the study.

690
01:11:10.987 --> 01:11:15.503
The murderer was in the passage.
Mr Boddy had been on the floor.

691
01:11:15.667 --> 01:11:18.135
He jumped up...

692
01:11:18.307 --> 01:11:22.061
The murderer came out.
picked up the candlestick...

693
01:11:22.227 --> 01:11:26.584
Mr Boddy followed us into the hall.
the murderer crept up behind him...

694
01:11:26.747 --> 01:11:30.706
- And killed him!
- Will you stop that?

695
01:11:30.867 --> 01:11:32.380
No.

696
01:11:32.547 --> 01:11:35.186
Then he threw him into the toilet.

697
01:11:35.347 --> 01:11:39.101
And joined us in the kitchen.
It took half a minute.

698
01:11:39.267 --> 01:11:43.260
- So who wasn't in the kitchen?
- That is the murderer.

699
01:11:47.067 --> 01:11:50.821
We put the weapons in here.
locked it. and ran to the door

700
01:11:50.987 --> 01:11:53.626
to throw away the key.

701
01:11:53.787 --> 01:11:55.186
The motorist!

702
01:11:55.347 --> 01:11:59.420
I put the key in my pocket. Someone
could have swapped it for another.

703
01:11:59.587 --> 01:12:03.136
- It could have been any one of us.
- Precisely.

704
01:12:03.307 --> 01:12:05.298
Wait a minute...

705
01:12:06.467 --> 01:12:09.027
Colonel Mustard has a top secret job.

706
01:12:09.187 --> 01:12:13.180
Mrs White's husband
was a nuclear physicist. and...

707
01:12:14.467 --> 01:12:17.106
Yvette is a link between them.

708
01:12:17.267 --> 01:12:20.623
- What is your job. Colonel?
- I can tell you.

709
01:12:20.787 --> 01:12:23.585
He's working on the next fusion bomb.

710
01:12:23.747 --> 01:12:27.103
- How did you know?
- Keep a secret? Me too.

711
01:12:27.267 --> 01:12:31.180
Was this a plot?
Or did Colonel Mustard do it alone?

712
01:12:31.347 --> 01:12:34.020
We'll see.
Let's look at the other murders.

713
01:12:34.187 --> 01:12:37.862
- Bad luck the motorist arrived.
- No luck. I invited him.

714
01:12:38.027 --> 01:12:40.416
- You did?
- It's obvious.

715
01:12:40.587 --> 01:12:43.465
Everyone was Mr Boddy's
victim or accomplice.

716
01:12:43.627 --> 01:12:47.142
Everyone who died gave him
information about one of you.

717
01:12:47.307 --> 01:12:50.026
I got them here to force him to confess.

718
01:12:50.187 --> 01:12:54.305
What about that motorist?
What information did he have?

719
01:12:54.467 --> 01:12:59.666
- He was my driver during the war.
- What was he holding over you?

720
01:12:59.827 --> 01:13:04.025
He knew that I was a war profiteer.

721
01:13:04.187 --> 01:13:09.102
I stole essential air force radio parts
and sold them on the black market.

722
01:13:09.267 --> 01:13:13.055
That's how I made my money.
It doesn't make me a murderer.

723
01:13:13.227 --> 01:13:17.220
A lot of our airmen died
because their radios didn't work.

724
01:13:17.387 --> 01:13:20.220
Was the policeman
working for Mr Boddy. too?

725
01:13:20.387 --> 01:13:23.140
The cop was from Washington.
on my payroll.

726
01:13:23.307 --> 01:13:28.142
I bribed him so I could carry on
with business. Mr Boddy found out.

727
01:13:28.307 --> 01:13:32.300
- Oh. my God!
- Oh. please!

728
01:13:32.467 --> 01:13:34.503
And the singing telegram girl?

729
01:13:39.027 --> 01:13:42.736
She was my patient once.
I had an affair with her.

730
01:13:42.907 --> 01:13:47.344
That's how I lost my licence.
Mr Boddy found that out. too.

731
01:13:47.507 --> 01:13:50.704
Let's put her in the study
with the others.

732
01:13:52.987 --> 01:13:56.263
So. now you all know why they died.

733
01:13:56.427 --> 01:14:00.022
Whoever killed Mr Boddy
wanted his accomplices dead.

734
01:14:00.187 --> 01:14:02.303
How did the murderer know?

735
01:14:02.467 --> 01:14:06.346
I guessed that the singer
informed on me to Mr Boddy.

736
01:14:06.507 --> 01:14:08.896
but I knew nothing of you until now.

737
01:14:09.067 --> 01:14:13.936
The murderer needed to get the weapons
and stole the key from my pocket.

738
01:14:14.107 --> 01:14:17.702
Then Colonel Mustard suggested
we search the house.

739
01:14:17.867 --> 01:14:20.779
That's right! It was his suggestion.

740
01:14:20.947 --> 01:14:24.417
One of us slipped away
and hurried to the study.

741
01:14:24.587 --> 01:14:28.865
On the desk was the envelope
containing photos and letters.

742
01:14:29.027 --> 01:14:31.541
the evidence of Mr Boddy's informants.

743
01:14:31.707 --> 01:14:35.143
- Where's the envelope now?
- Gone.

744
01:14:35.307 --> 01:14:40.062
Destroyed. Perhaps in the fire.
the only possible place.

745
01:14:42.267 --> 01:14:47.660
Aha...! Then the murderer
went to the cupboard.

746
01:14:47.827 --> 01:14:49.818
unlocked it. took the wrench...

747
01:14:49.987 --> 01:14:54.822
Then we found the passage to
the lounge and found the motorist dead.

748
01:14:54.987 --> 01:14:58.502
That's right! We couldn't get in.
so we went back.

749
01:14:58.667 --> 01:15:04.583
got the gun and shot the door open.
bang! And then the doorbell rang.

750
01:15:05.507 --> 01:15:09.978
Whoever it is must go away
or they'll be killed.

751
01:15:12.427 --> 01:15:15.817
Have you ever thought
about the kingdom of heaven?

752
01:15:15.987 --> 01:15:19.741
- What?
- The kingdom of heaven is at hand.

753
01:15:19.907 --> 01:15:23.297
- You ain't kiddin'
- Armageddon is almost upon us.

754
01:15:23.467 --> 01:15:25.935
- It's already here!
- Go away!

755
01:15:26.107 --> 01:15:31.135
- Your souls are in danger.
- Our lives are in danger. you beatnik!

756
01:15:31.307 --> 01:15:36.745
The cop came. we put him in the library.
We forgot the open cupboard. split up.

757
01:15:36.947 --> 01:15:40.019
And the murderer
switched off the electricity.

758
01:15:40.187 --> 01:15:43.463
- Oh. my God!
- Turn on the lights!

759
01:15:44.987 --> 01:15:50.186
- Didn't mean to frighten you.
- Bit late for that... I hate that!

760
01:15:50.347 --> 01:15:55.262
Then came three more murders.
None of us killed Mr Boddy or the cook.

761
01:15:55.427 --> 01:15:58.817
- So who did?!
- The one person who wasn't with us.

762
01:16:00.987 --> 01:16:02.818
- Yvette.
- Yvette!

763
01:16:02.987 --> 01:16:07.617
She was listening to us. She heard
the shot and thought he was dead.

764
01:16:07.787 --> 01:16:12.224
While we examined the bullet-hole.
she got the dagger. ran to the kitchen.

765
01:16:12.387 --> 01:16:17.780
and stabbed the cook. We heard nothing
because Mrs Peacock was screaming.

766
01:16:17.947 --> 01:16:21.144
Yvette returned.
screamed and we ran to her.

767
01:16:21.307 --> 01:16:24.185
- When did she kill Mr Boddy?
- When I said.

768
01:16:24.347 --> 01:16:28.943
We ran to see the cook. Yvette
checked that Mr Boddy was dead.

769
01:16:29.107 --> 01:16:34.704
He followed into the hall. she hit him on
the head and dragged him to the toilet.

770
01:16:34.867 --> 01:16:36.983
- Why?
- To create confusion.

771
01:16:37.147 --> 01:16:39.741
- It worked.
- Why did she do it?

772
01:16:39.907 --> 01:16:44.059
Was she obeying orders
from the person who later killed her?

773
01:16:44.227 --> 01:16:45.546
- Who?
- Who?

774
01:16:45.707 --> 01:16:47.504
Who?

775
01:16:47.667 --> 01:16:51.376
Was it one of her clients?

776
01:16:51.547 --> 01:16:56.257
Or was it a jealous wife?
Or an adulterous doctor?

777
01:16:56.427 --> 01:17:00.739
- No. it was her employer. miss Scarlet.
- That's a lie.

778
01:17:00.907 --> 01:17:05.298
Is it? You used her
the way you always used her.

779
01:17:05.467 --> 01:17:07.617
You killed the motorist.

780
01:17:07.787 --> 01:17:11.541
- How did I know about the passage?
- Yvette told you.

781
01:17:11.707 --> 01:17:17.100
When we split up again.
you switched off the electricity.

782
01:17:17.267 --> 01:17:21.101
You got the lead pipe and the rope.
strangled Yvette.

783
01:17:21.267 --> 01:17:26.295
ran to the library. killed the cop.
picked up the gun.

784
01:17:26.467 --> 01:17:32.463
opened the door. recognised the singer
from her photo. and shot her.

785
01:17:32.627 --> 01:17:35.824
- You've no proof.
- The gun is missing.

786
01:17:35.987 --> 01:17:40.060
Gentlemen. turn out your pockets.
Ladies. empty your purses.

787
01:17:40.227 --> 01:17:42.741
Whoever has the gun is the murderer.

788
01:17:43.827 --> 01:17:46.136
Brilliant! I congratulate you.

789
01:17:46.307 --> 01:17:48.696
- Me too!
- Shut up!

790
01:17:48.867 --> 01:17:51.779
- One thing I don't understand.
- One thing?

791
01:17:51.947 --> 01:17:55.098
Why? Half of Washington
knows your business.

792
01:17:55.267 --> 01:17:59.499
You were in no danger. The whole town
would be implicated with you.

793
01:17:59.667 --> 01:18:04.138
They don't know
that my real business is secrets.

794
01:18:04.307 --> 01:18:06.775
And Yvette found them out for me.

795
01:18:06.947 --> 01:18:10.257
The secrets of Senator Peacock's
defence committee.

796
01:18:10.427 --> 01:18:16.423
Colonel Mustard's fusion bomb.
Professor Plum's UN contacts.

797
01:18:16.587 --> 01:18:21.820
and the work of your husband.
the nuclear physicist.

798
01:18:21.987 --> 01:18:24.820
So. it is political. You're a communist!

799
01:18:24.987 --> 01:18:28.946
No. Mr Green.
Communism is just a red herring.

800
01:18:29.107 --> 01:18:33.817
Like all prostitutes. I'm a capitalist
and I'm going to sell my secrets.

801
01:18:33.987 --> 01:18:36.979
your secrets. to the highest bidder.

802
01:18:37.147 --> 01:18:41.857
- What if we don't cooperate?
- You will. or I'll expose you.

803
01:18:42.027 --> 01:18:47.863
- We could expose you. Six murders...
- It won't help your reputation at the UN.

804
01:18:48.027 --> 01:18:52.657
You're implicated not only in adultery
with a patient but in her death.

805
01:18:52.827 --> 01:18:58.424
- And the deaths of five others.
- You don't know the UN. it might help.

806
01:18:58.587 --> 01:19:03.297
- It's no good. I've no more money.
- Neither do I.

807
01:19:03.467 --> 01:19:08.780
I know. But you can pay me
in government information. all of you.

808
01:19:09.907 --> 01:19:12.137
Except you. Wadsworth.

809
01:19:12.307 --> 01:19:16.698
As a butler. you have no access
to government secrets.

810
01:19:16.867 --> 01:19:19.939
So. I'm afraid your moment has come.

811
01:19:20.107 --> 01:19:23.816
- Not so fast! I do have a secret or two.
- Such as?

812
01:19:23.987 --> 01:19:26.865
Game's up.
There are no bullets in that gun.

813
01:19:27.027 --> 01:19:30.178
- I'm not falling for that trick.
- It's no trick.

814
01:19:30.347 --> 01:19:34.943
One for Boddy. two for the chandelier.
two at the door and one for the singer.

815
01:19:35.107 --> 01:19:38.304
- That's not six.
- One plus two plus two plus one.

816
01:19:38.467 --> 01:19:41.379
One for the chandelier.
One plus two plus one plus one.

817
01:19:41.547 --> 01:19:46.746
That's one plus one plus two plus one.
Not one plus two plus one plus one.

818
01:19:46.907 --> 01:19:49.137
One plus two plus... shut up!

819
01:19:49.307 --> 01:19:53.505
The point is. there's one bullet.
and guess who's gonna get it?

820
01:20:03.587 --> 01:20:06.545
I'm only a guest!

821
01:20:08.107 --> 01:20:10.780
Where's the chief?

822
01:20:11.507 --> 01:20:13.657
Well done. Wadsworth.

823
01:20:13.827 --> 01:20:18.298
I warned you. Mr Hoover
is an expert on Armageddon.

824
01:20:18.467 --> 01:20:21.425
Don't hate me for trying to shoot you.

825
01:20:21.587 --> 01:20:26.456
Frankly. Scarlet. I don't give a damn.
There are no bullets in this gun.

826
01:20:30.987 --> 01:20:34.138
One plus two... plus one...

827
01:20:34.307 --> 01:20:37.265
Plus two. plus one... is...

828
01:20:51.507 --> 01:20:54.305
In the dark.
the murderer ran to the study.

829
01:20:54.467 --> 01:20:57.504
got the rope and lead pipe.
ran to the billiard-room.

830
01:20:57.667 --> 01:21:00.261
strangled Yvette...

831
01:21:01.267 --> 01:21:06.466
Ran to the library. hit the cop.
The doorbell. it was the singing telegram.

832
01:21:06.627 --> 01:21:12.259
The murderer picked up the gun. ran
to the door. recognised and shot the girl.

833
01:21:12.427 --> 01:21:15.419
- Then ran back to the cellar.
- The cellar!

834
01:21:15.587 --> 01:21:21.378
- Colonel Mustard wasn't in the cellar!
- No... but you were!

835
01:21:22.227 --> 01:21:23.546
So?

836
01:21:23.707 --> 01:21:27.017
You were missing
when the cook and Mr Boddy died.

837
01:21:27.187 --> 01:21:32.181
The cook used to be your cook.
Remember your fatal mistake?

838
01:21:32.347 --> 01:21:36.056
You told us at dinner
we were eating your favourite dish.

839
01:21:36.227 --> 01:21:39.458
Monkey's brains.
though popular in Cantonese cuisine.

840
01:21:39.667 --> 01:21:42.056
are not often found in Washington DC.

841
01:21:42.227 --> 01:21:44.218
Is that what we ate?

842
01:21:44.387 --> 01:21:48.619
- Why murder the others?
- In case Mr Boddy'd told them of you.

843
01:21:48.787 --> 01:21:53.178
It was nothing to do with a nuclear
physicist and the fusion bomb?

844
01:21:53.347 --> 01:21:58.262
No. communism was a red herring.
Mrs Peacock did it all.

845
01:21:58.427 --> 01:22:02.022
- There's no proof.
- The gun is missing.

846
01:22:02.187 --> 01:22:05.941
Gentlemen. turn out your pockets.
Ladies. empty your purses.

847
01:22:06.107 --> 01:22:08.462
Whoever has the gun is the murderer.

848
01:22:08.627 --> 01:22:10.026
Very well.

849
01:22:11.187 --> 01:22:14.816
What do you propose to do about it?

850
01:22:14.987 --> 01:22:16.978
- Nothing.
- Nothing?

851
01:22:17.147 --> 01:22:21.857
Nothing. I don't approve of murder.
but you've done the world a service

852
01:22:22.067 --> 01:22:25.503
by ridding it of a blackmailer
and his informers.

853
01:22:25.667 --> 01:22:30.024
- The police will be here any minute.
- Why? Nobody's called them.

854
01:22:30.187 --> 01:22:33.099
- You mean?
- That's right!

855
01:22:33.267 --> 01:22:37.579
I suggest we stack the bodies
in the cellar. lock it.

856
01:22:37.747 --> 01:22:42.775
leave quietly one at a time
and pretend none of this ever happened.

857
01:22:42.947 --> 01:22:47.623
Great idea! I'll leave first.
if you don't mind.

858
01:22:48.747 --> 01:22:53.537
Be my guest. In fact. I think
we all owe you a vote of thanks.

859
01:22:55.227 --> 01:22:59.459
<i>For she's a jolly good fellow</i>
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>

860
01:22:59.627 --> 01:23:03.506
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>

861
01:23:03.667 --> 01:23:05.737
<i>which nobody can deny</i>

862
01:23:05.907 --> 01:23:10.059
<i>which nobody can deny</i>
<i>which nobody can deny</i>

863
01:23:10.227 --> 01:23:14.266
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>

864
01:23:14.427 --> 01:23:16.224
<i>for she's a jolly...</i>

865
01:23:16.387 --> 01:23:20.266
- I said I didn't do it!
- What if the authorities find out?

866
01:23:20.427 --> 01:23:22.702
- The FBI will take care of that.
- You mean...

867
01:23:22.867 --> 01:23:27.987
Mr Hoover? I work for him. of course.
How else could I know all about you?

868
01:23:28.147 --> 01:23:31.742
- One thing I don't understand.
- One thing?

869
01:23:31.907 --> 01:23:34.262
Who was bribing Mrs Peacock?

870
01:23:34.427 --> 01:23:37.783
A foreign power.
Her husband handles defence contracts.

871
01:23:37.947 --> 01:23:42.225
- Will there be a cover-up?
- Yes. what's to be gained by exposure?

872
01:23:42.387 --> 01:23:45.106
Do the FBI clean up
after multiple murder?

873
01:23:45.267 --> 01:23:49.306
Yes. Why do you think it's run
by a man called Hoover?

874
01:23:53.707 --> 01:23:56.505
Mrs Peacock?

875
01:23:58.427 --> 01:24:02.784
- How did you know my name?
- The kingdom of heaven is at hand.

876
01:24:03.787 --> 01:24:06.585
OK. take her away.

877
01:24:08.427 --> 01:24:13.342
Take your hands off me.
I'm a senator's wife!

878
01:24:13.507 --> 01:24:15.941
Wadsworth. we got her.

879
01:24:16.107 --> 01:24:19.782
See? Like the mounties.
we always get our man.

880
01:24:19.947 --> 01:24:22.256
Mrs Peacock was a man?

881
01:24:23.867 --> 01:24:26.904
Would anyone care for fruit. or dessert?

882
01:24:38.707 --> 01:24:42.461
- Didn't mean to frighten anyone.
- Bit late for that!

883
01:24:42.627 --> 01:24:45.539
- Then three more murders.
- So who did it?!

884
01:24:45.707 --> 01:24:48.904
Let's consider each murder one by one.

885
01:24:49.067 --> 01:24:52.139
Professor Plum.
you knew Mr Boddy was still alive.

886
01:24:52.307 --> 01:24:56.061
Even psychiatrists can tell
if patients are alive or dead.

887
01:24:56.227 --> 01:25:00.505
You fired the gun in the dark. missed.
and pretended he was dead.

888
01:25:00.667 --> 01:25:03.659
You were able to kill him later.
unobserved.

889
01:25:03.827 --> 01:25:07.502
He was missing in the kitchen
when we found the cook.

890
01:25:07.667 --> 01:25:12.422
He was with us when we found Yvette.
so how did he kill the cook?

891
01:25:12.587 --> 01:25:15.420
- I didn't.
- Expect us to believe that?

892
01:25:15.587 --> 01:25:19.421
I expect you to believe it.
You killed the cook.

893
01:25:19.587 --> 01:25:23.057
She informed on you to Mr Boddy.
You made one mistake.

894
01:25:23.227 --> 01:25:28.460
Sitting here. Mrs Peacock said she was
eating one of her favourite recipes.

895
01:25:28.627 --> 01:25:32.415
And monkeys' brains.
though popular in Cantonese cuisine.

896
01:25:32.587 --> 01:25:35.738
are not often found in Washington DC.

897
01:25:35.907 --> 01:25:39.024
Colonel. when we saw the motorist
at the door.

898
01:25:39.187 --> 01:25:43.499
you took the key to the cupboard
and suggested we split up.

899
01:25:43.667 --> 01:25:46.261
You left miss Scarlet.
crossed the hall.

900
01:25:46.427 --> 01:25:49.624
opened the cupboard. took the wrench.

901
01:25:49.787 --> 01:25:52.745
entered the lounge.
killed the motorist with a blow.

902
01:25:52.907 --> 01:25:54.898
Like that!

903
01:25:56.907 --> 01:26:01.139
- This is incredible!
- Not compared to what happened next.

904
01:26:01.307 --> 01:26:04.424
I went upstairs with you. Mrs White.

905
01:26:04.587 --> 01:26:07.977
And. while I was in the master bedroom.

906
01:26:08.147 --> 01:26:11.583
you hurried downstairs.
turned off the electricity.

907
01:26:11.747 --> 01:26:15.057
got the rope. and throttled Yvette.

908
01:26:15.227 --> 01:26:19.300
You were jealous of your husband
and Yvette so you killed him. too.

909
01:26:19.467 --> 01:26:21.458
Yes.

910
01:26:23.667 --> 01:26:26.181
Yes. I did it. I killed Yvette.

911
01:26:26.347 --> 01:26:30.306
I hated her so much...

912
01:26:30.467 --> 01:26:32.901
It. it... flames...

913
01:26:33.067 --> 01:26:36.423
Flames on the side of my face...

914
01:26:36.587 --> 01:26:40.341
Breathing. breath. heaving breaths...

915
01:26:40.507 --> 01:26:44.978
While we were in the billiard-room.
miss Scarlet crossed to the library.

916
01:26:45.147 --> 01:26:48.617
and hit the cop she'd been bribing
with a lead pipe.

917
01:26:48.787 --> 01:26:53.383
- True or false?
- True. Who are you? Perry Mason?

918
01:26:53.547 --> 01:26:56.778
- Mr green must have shot the singer.
- I didn't!

919
01:26:56.947 --> 01:26:59.825
- There's nobody else left.
- I didn't do it.

920
01:26:59.987 --> 01:27:03.821
The gun is missing.
Whoever's got the gun shot the girl.

921
01:27:03.987 --> 01:27:06.182
- I shot her.
- You?!

922
01:27:08.027 --> 01:27:10.541
I was going to expose you.

923
01:27:10.707 --> 01:27:14.541
- I choose to expose myself.
- Please! Ladies present.

924
01:27:14.707 --> 01:27:20.100
You thought Mr Boddy was dead. Why?
None of you had met him before.

925
01:27:20.267 --> 01:27:22.940
You're Mr Boddy!

926
01:27:23.107 --> 01:27:24.825
Wait!

927
01:27:24.987 --> 01:27:27.137
- Who did I kill?
- My butler.

928
01:27:27.307 --> 01:27:29.298
Oh. shucks.

929
01:27:30.547 --> 01:27:32.663
He was expendable. like you.

930
01:27:32.827 --> 01:27:36.217
I'm grateful to you
for disposing of my informers.

931
01:27:36.387 --> 01:27:39.618
Saved me the trouble
of destroying the evidence.

932
01:27:39.787 --> 01:27:43.496
This has nothing to do
with my nuclear physicist husband

933
01:27:43.667 --> 01:27:47.023
or Colonel Mustard's work
with the fusion bomb?

934
01:27:47.187 --> 01:27:50.020
No. communism was just a red herring.

935
01:27:52.227 --> 01:27:56.186
The police are coming.
You'll never get away with it.

936
01:27:56.347 --> 01:27:59.066
Why should the police come?
Nobody's called them.

937
01:27:59.227 --> 01:28:01.741
- You mean...
- Oh. my God! Of course!

938
01:28:01.907 --> 01:28:05.582
Why shouldn't we escape?
Put the bodies in the cellar.

939
01:28:05.747 --> 01:28:09.296
leave quietly and forget
any of this ever happened.

940
01:28:09.467 --> 01:28:14.336
- And you'll go on blackmailing us.
- Of course. why not?

941
01:28:14.507 --> 01:28:16.782
Well. I'll tell you why not.

942
01:28:19.507 --> 01:28:22.101
Good shot. green.

943
01:28:32.827 --> 01:28:34.943
Very good.

944
01:28:43.107 --> 01:28:45.302
- You a cop?
- I'm a plant.

945
01:28:45.467 --> 01:28:49.176
- A plant? Men like you are called fruits.
- Very funny.

946
01:28:49.347 --> 01:28:52.623
FBI. That call from J Edgar Hoover
was for me.

947
01:28:55.267 --> 01:28:57.497
I told you I didn't do it.

948
01:29:03.667 --> 01:29:06.181
- All right. Who done it?
- He did it.

949
01:29:06.347 --> 01:29:08.099
- That gentleman...
- No!

950
01:29:08.267 --> 01:29:10.383
They all did it.

951
01:29:11.467 --> 01:29:15.062
But if you wanna know
who killed Mr Boddy. I did.

952
01:29:15.227 --> 01:29:18.537
In the hall. with the revolver.

953
01:29:18.707 --> 01:29:22.825
OK. chief. Take 'em away.
I'm going home to sleep with my wife.

954
01:32:51.073 --> 01:32:56.272
- Didn't mean to frighten you.
- Bit late for that... I hate that!

955
01:32:56.433 --> 01:33:01.348
Then came three more murders.
None of us killed Mr Boddy or the cook.

956
01:33:01.513 --> 01:33:04.903
- So who did?!
- The one person who wasn't with us.

957
01:33:07.073 --> 01:33:08.904
- Yvette.
- Yvette!

958
01:33:09.073 --> 01:33:13.703
She was listening to us. She heard
the shot and thought he was dead.

959
01:33:13.873 --> 01:33:18.310
While we examined the bullet-hole.
she got the dagger. ran to the kitchen.

960
01:33:18.473 --> 01:33:23.866
and stabbed the cook. We heard nothing
because Mrs Peacock was screaming.

961
01:33:24.033 --> 01:33:27.230
Yvette returned.
screamed and we ran to her.

962
01:33:27.393 --> 01:33:30.271
- When did she kill Mr Boddy?
- When I said.

963
01:33:30.433 --> 01:33:35.029
We ran to see the cook. Yvette
checked that Mr Boddy was dead.

964
01:33:35.193 --> 01:33:40.790
He followed into the hall. she hit him on
the head and dragged him to the toilet.

965
01:33:40.953 --> 01:33:43.069
- Why?
- To create confusion.

966
01:33:43.233 --> 01:33:45.827
- It worked.
- Why did she do it?

967
01:33:45.993 --> 01:33:50.145
Was she obeying orders
from the person who later killed her?

968
01:33:50.313 --> 01:33:51.632
- Who?
- Who?

969
01:33:51.793 --> 01:33:53.590
Who?

970
01:33:53.753 --> 01:33:57.462
Was it one of her clients?

971
01:33:57.633 --> 01:34:02.343
Or was it a jealous wife?
Or an adulterous doctor?

972
01:34:02.513 --> 01:34:06.825
- No. it was her employer. miss Scarlet.
- That's a lie.

973
01:34:06.993 --> 01:34:11.384
Is it? You used her
the way you always used her.

974
01:34:11.553 --> 01:34:13.703
You killed the motorist.

975
01:34:13.873 --> 01:34:17.627
- How did I know about the passage?
- Yvette told you.

976
01:34:17.793 --> 01:34:23.186
When we split up again.
you switched off the electricity.

977
01:34:23.353 --> 01:34:27.187
You got the lead pipe and the rope.
strangled Yvette.

978
01:34:27.353 --> 01:34:32.381
ran to the library. killed the cop.
picked up the gun.

979
01:34:32.553 --> 01:34:38.549
opened the door. recognised the singer
from her photo. and shot her.

980
01:34:38.713 --> 01:34:41.910
- You've no proof.
- The gun is missing.

981
01:34:42.073 --> 01:34:46.146
Gentlemen. turn out your pockets.
Ladies. empty your purses.

982
01:34:46.313 --> 01:34:48.827
Whoever has the gun is the murderer.

983
01:34:49.913 --> 01:34:52.222
Brilliant! I congratulate you.

984
01:34:52.393 --> 01:34:54.782
- Me too!
- Shut up!

985
01:34:54.953 --> 01:34:57.865
- One thing I don't understand.
- One thing?

986
01:34:58.033 --> 01:35:01.184
Why? Half of Washington
knows your business.

987
01:35:01.353 --> 01:35:05.585
You were in no danger. The whole town
would be implicated with you.

988
01:35:05.753 --> 01:35:10.224
They don't know
that my real business is secrets.

989
01:35:10.393 --> 01:35:12.861
And Yvette found them out for me.

990
01:35:13.033 --> 01:35:16.343
The secrets of Senator Peacock's
defence committee.

991
01:35:16.513 --> 01:35:22.509
Colonel Mustard's fusion bomb.
Professor Plum's UN contacts.

992
01:35:22.673 --> 01:35:27.906
and the work of your husband.
the nuclear physicist.

993
01:35:28.073 --> 01:35:30.906
So. it is political. You're a communist!

994
01:35:31.073 --> 01:35:35.032
No. Mr Green.
Communism is just a red herring.

995
01:35:35.193 --> 01:35:39.903
Like all prostitutes. I'm a capitalist
and I'm going to sell my secrets.

996
01:35:40.073 --> 01:35:43.065
your secrets. to the highest bidder.

997
01:35:43.233 --> 01:35:47.943
- What if we don't cooperate?
- You will. or I'll expose you.

998
01:35:48.113 --> 01:35:53.949
- We could expose you. Six murders...
- It won't help your reputation at the UN.

999
01:35:54.113 --> 01:35:58.743
You're implicated not only in adultery
with a patient but in her death.

1000
01:35:58.913 --> 01:36:04.510
- And the deaths of five others.
- You don't know the UN. it might help.

1001
01:36:04.673 --> 01:36:09.383
- It's no good. I've no more money.
- Neither do I.

1002
01:36:09.553 --> 01:36:14.866
I know. But you can pay me
in government information. all of you.

1003
01:36:15.993 --> 01:36:18.223
Except you. Wadsworth.

1004
01:36:18.393 --> 01:36:22.784
As a butler. you have no access
to government secrets.

1005
01:36:22.953 --> 01:36:26.025
So. I'm afraid your moment has come.

1006
01:36:26.193 --> 01:36:29.902
- Not so fast! I do have a secret or two.
- Such as?

1007
01:36:30.073 --> 01:36:32.951
Game's up.
There are no bullets in that gun.

1008
01:36:33.113 --> 01:36:36.264
- I'm not falling for that trick.
- It's no trick.

1009
01:36:36.433 --> 01:36:41.029
One for Boddy. two for the chandelier.
two at the door and one for the singer.

1010
01:36:41.193 --> 01:36:44.390
- That's not six.
- One plus two plus two plus one.

1011
01:36:44.553 --> 01:36:47.465
One for the chandelier.
One plus two plus one plus one.

1012
01:36:47.633 --> 01:36:52.832
That's one plus one plus two plus one.
Not one plus two plus one plus one.

1013
01:36:52.993 --> 01:36:55.223
One plus two plus... shut up!

1014
01:36:55.393 --> 01:36:59.591
The point is. there's one bullet.
and guess who's gonna get it?

1015
01:37:09.673 --> 01:37:12.631
I'm only a guest!

1016
01:37:14.193 --> 01:37:16.866
Where's the chief?

1017
01:37:17.593 --> 01:37:19.743
Well done. Wadsworth.

1018
01:37:19.913 --> 01:37:24.384
I warned you. Mr Hoover
is an expert on Armageddon.

1019
01:37:24.553 --> 01:37:27.511
Don't hate me for trying to shoot you.

1020
01:37:27.673 --> 01:37:32.542
Frankly. Scarlet. I don't give a damn.
There are no bullets in this gun.

1021
01:37:37.073 --> 01:37:40.224
One plus two... plus one...

1022
01:37:40.393 --> 01:37:43.351
Plus two. plus one... is...

1023
01:41:12.013 --> 01:41:14.811
In the dark.
the murderer ran to the study.

1024
01:41:14.973 --> 01:41:18.010
got the rope and lead pipe.
ran to the billiard-room.

1025
01:41:18.173 --> 01:41:20.767
strangled Yvette...

1026
01:41:21.773 --> 01:41:26.972
Ran to the library. hit the cop.
The doorbell. it was the singing telegram.

1027
01:41:27.133 --> 01:41:32.765
The murderer picked up the gun. ran
to the door. recognised and shot the girl.

1028
01:41:32.933 --> 01:41:35.925
- Then ran back to the cellar.
- The cellar!

1029
01:41:36.093 --> 01:41:41.884
- Colonel Mustard wasn't in the cellar!
- No... but you were!

1030
01:41:42.733 --> 01:41:44.052
So?

1031
01:41:44.213 --> 01:41:47.523
You were missing
when the cook and Mr Boddy died.

1032
01:41:47.693 --> 01:41:52.687
The cook used to be your cook.
Remember your fatal mistake?

1033
01:41:52.853 --> 01:41:56.562
You told us at dinner
we were eating your favourite dish.

1034
01:41:56.733 --> 01:41:59.964
Monkey's brains.
though popular in Cantonese cuisine.

1035
01:42:00.173 --> 01:42:02.562
are not often found in Washington DC.

1036
01:42:02.733 --> 01:42:04.724
Is that what we ate?

1037
01:42:04.893 --> 01:42:09.125
- Why murder the others?
- In case Mr Boddy'd told them of you.

1038
01:42:09.293 --> 01:42:13.684
It was nothing to do with a nuclear
physicist and the fusion bomb?

1039
01:42:13.853 --> 01:42:18.768
No. communism was a red herring.
Mrs Peacock did it all.

1040
01:42:18.933 --> 01:42:22.528
- There's no proof.
- The gun is missing.

1041
01:42:22.693 --> 01:42:26.447
Gentlemen. turn out your pockets.
Ladies. empty your purses.

1042
01:42:26.613 --> 01:42:28.968
Whoever has the gun is the murderer.

1043
01:42:29.133 --> 01:42:30.532
Very well.

1044
01:42:31.693 --> 01:42:35.322
What do you propose to do about it?

1045
01:42:35.493 --> 01:42:37.484
- Nothing.
- Nothing?

1046
01:42:37.653 --> 01:42:42.363
Nothing. I don't approve of murder.
but you've done the world a service

1047
01:42:42.573 --> 01:42:46.009
by ridding it of a blackmailer
and his informers.

1048
01:42:46.173 --> 01:42:50.530
- The police will be here any minute.
- Why? Nobody's called them.

1049
01:42:50.693 --> 01:42:53.605
- You mean?
- That's right!

1050
01:42:53.773 --> 01:42:58.085
I suggest we stack the bodies
in the cellar. lock it.

1051
01:42:58.253 --> 01:43:03.281
leave quietly one at a time
and pretend none of this ever happened.

1052
01:43:03.453 --> 01:43:08.129
Great idea! I'll leave first.
if you don't mind.

1053
01:43:09.253 --> 01:43:14.043
Be my guest. In fact. I think
we all owe you a vote of thanks.

1054
01:43:15.733 --> 01:43:19.965
<i>For she's a jolly good fellow</i>
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>

1055
01:43:20.133 --> 01:43:24.012
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>

1056
01:43:24.173 --> 01:43:26.243
<i>which nobody can deny</i>

1057
01:43:26.413 --> 01:43:30.565
<i>which nobody can deny</i>
<i>which nobody can deny</i>

1058
01:43:30.733 --> 01:43:34.772
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>
<i>for she's a jolly good fellow</i>

1059
01:43:34.933 --> 01:43:36.730
<i>for she's a jolly...</i>

1060
01:43:36.893 --> 01:43:40.772
- I said I didn't do it!
- What if the authorities find out?

1061
01:43:40.933 --> 01:43:43.208
- The FBI will take care of that.
- You mean...

1062
01:43:43.373 --> 01:43:48.493
Mr Hoover? I work for him. of course.
How else could I know all about you?

1063
01:43:48.653 --> 01:43:52.248
- One thing I don't understand.
- One thing?

1064
01:43:52.413 --> 01:43:54.768
Who was bribing Mrs Peacock?

1065
01:43:54.933 --> 01:43:58.289
A foreign power.
Her husband handles defence contracts.

1066
01:43:58.453 --> 01:44:02.731
- Will there be a cover-up?
- Yes. what's to be gained by exposure?

1067
01:44:02.893 --> 01:44:05.612
Do the FBI clean up
after multiple murder?

1068
01:44:05.773 --> 01:44:09.812
Yes. Why do you think it's run
by a man called Hoover?

1069
01:44:14.213 --> 01:44:17.011
Mrs Peacock?

1070
01:44:18.933 --> 01:44:23.290
- How did you know my name?
- The kingdom of heaven is at hand.

1071
01:44:24.293 --> 01:44:27.091
OK. take her away.

1072
01:44:28.933 --> 01:44:33.848
Take your hands off me.
I'm a senator's wife!

1073
01:44:34.013 --> 01:44:36.447
Wadsworth. we got her.

1074
01:44:36.613 --> 01:44:40.288
See? Like the mounties.
we always get our man.

1075
01:44:40.453 --> 01:44:42.762
Mrs Peacock was a man?

1076
01:44:44.373 --> 01:44:47.410
Would anyone care for fruit. or dessert?

1077
01:48:13.812 --> 01:48:17.566
- Didn't mean to frighten anyone.
- Bit late for that!

1078
01:48:17.732 --> 01:48:20.644
- Then three more murders.
- So who did it?!

1079
01:48:20.812 --> 01:48:24.009
Let's consider each murder one by one.

1080
01:48:24.172 --> 01:48:27.244
Professor Plum.
you knew Mr Boddy was still alive.

1081
01:48:27.412 --> 01:48:31.166
Even psychiatrists can tell
if patients are alive or dead.

1082
01:48:31.332 --> 01:48:35.610
You fired the gun in the dark. missed.
and pretended he was dead.

1083
01:48:35.772 --> 01:48:38.764
You were able to kill him later.
unobserved.

1084
01:48:38.932 --> 01:48:42.607
He was missing in the kitchen
when we found the cook.

1085
01:48:42.772 --> 01:48:47.527
He was with us when we found Yvette.
so how did he kill the cook?

1086
01:48:47.692 --> 01:48:50.525
- I didn't.
- Expect us to believe that?

1087
01:48:50.692 --> 01:48:54.526
I expect you to believe it.
You killed the cook.

1088
01:48:54.692 --> 01:48:58.162
She informed on you to Mr Boddy.
You made one mistake.

1089
01:48:58.332 --> 01:49:03.565
Sitting here. Mrs Peacock said she was
eating one of her favourite recipes.

1090
01:49:03.732 --> 01:49:07.520
And monkeys' brains.
though popular in Cantonese cuisine.

1091
01:49:07.692 --> 01:49:10.843
are not often found in Washington DC.

1092
01:49:11.012 --> 01:49:14.129
Colonel. when we saw the motorist
at the door.

1093
01:49:14.292 --> 01:49:18.604
you took the key to the cupboard
and suggested we split up.

1094
01:49:18.772 --> 01:49:21.366
You left miss Scarlet.
crossed the hall.

1095
01:49:21.532 --> 01:49:24.729
opened the cupboard. took the wrench.

1096
01:49:24.892 --> 01:49:27.850
entered the lounge.
killed the motorist with a blow.

1097
01:49:28.012 --> 01:49:30.003
Like that!

1098
01:49:32.012 --> 01:49:36.244
- This is incredible!
- Not compared to what happened next.

1099
01:49:36.412 --> 01:49:39.529
I went upstairs with you. Mrs White.

1100
01:49:39.692 --> 01:49:43.082
And. while I was in the master bedroom.

1101
01:49:43.252 --> 01:49:46.688
you hurried downstairs.
turned off the electricity.

1102
01:49:46.852 --> 01:49:50.162
got the rope. and throttled Yvette.

1103
01:49:50.332 --> 01:49:54.405
You were jealous of your husband
and Yvette so you killed him. too.

1104
01:49:54.572 --> 01:49:56.563
Yes.

1105
01:49:58.772 --> 01:50:01.286
Yes. I did it. I killed Yvette.

1106
01:50:01.452 --> 01:50:05.411
I hated her so much...

1107
01:50:05.572 --> 01:50:08.006
It. it... flames...

1108
01:50:08.172 --> 01:50:11.528
Flames on the side of my face...

1109
01:50:11.692 --> 01:50:15.446
Breathing. breath. heaving breaths...

1110
01:50:15.612 --> 01:50:20.083
While we were in the billiard-room.
miss Scarlet crossed to the library.

1111
01:50:20.252 --> 01:50:23.722
and hit the cop she'd been bribing
with a lead pipe.

1112
01:50:23.892 --> 01:50:28.488
- True or false?
- True. Who are you? Perry Mason?

1113
01:50:28.652 --> 01:50:31.883
- Mr green must have shot the singer.
- I didn't!

1114
01:50:32.052 --> 01:50:34.930
- There's nobody else left.
- I didn't do it.

1115
01:50:35.092 --> 01:50:38.926
The gun is missing.
Whoever's got the gun shot the girl.

1116
01:50:39.092 --> 01:50:41.287
- I shot her.
- You?!

1117
01:50:43.132 --> 01:50:45.646
I was going to expose you.

1118
01:50:45.812 --> 01:50:49.646
- I choose to expose myself.
- Please! Ladies present.

1119
01:50:49.812 --> 01:50:55.205
You thought Mr Boddy was dead. Why?
None of you had met him before.

1120
01:50:55.372 --> 01:50:58.045
You're Mr Boddy!

1121
01:50:58.212 --> 01:50:59.930
Wait!

1122
01:51:00.092 --> 01:51:02.242
- Who did I kill?
- My butler.

1123
01:51:02.412 --> 01:51:04.403
Oh. shucks.

1124
01:51:05.652 --> 01:51:07.768
He was expendable. like you.

1125
01:51:07.932 --> 01:51:11.322
I'm grateful to you
for disposing of my informers.

1126
01:51:11.492 --> 01:51:14.723
Saved me the trouble
of destroying the evidence.

1127
01:51:14.892 --> 01:51:18.601
This has nothing to do
with my nuclear physicist husband

1128
01:51:18.772 --> 01:51:22.128
or Colonel Mustard's work
with the fusion bomb?

1129
01:51:22.292 --> 01:51:25.125
No. communism was just a red herring.

1130
01:51:27.332 --> 01:51:31.291
The police are coming.
You'll never get away with it.

1131
01:51:31.452 --> 01:51:34.171
Why should the police come?
Nobody's called them.

1132
01:51:34.332 --> 01:51:36.846
- You mean...
- Oh. my God! Of course!

1133
01:51:37.012 --> 01:51:40.687
Why shouldn't we escape?
Put the bodies in the cellar.

1134
01:51:40.852 --> 01:51:44.401
leave quietly and forget
any of this ever happened.

1135
01:51:44.572 --> 01:51:49.441
- And you'll go on blackmailing us.
- Of course. why not?

1136
01:51:49.612 --> 01:51:51.887
Well. I'll tell you why not.

1137
01:51:54.612 --> 01:51:57.206
Good shot. green.

1138
01:52:07.932 --> 01:52:10.048
Very good.

1139
01:52:18.212 --> 01:52:20.407
- You a cop?
- I'm a plant.

1140
01:52:20.572 --> 01:52:24.281
- A plant? Men like you are called fruits.
- Very funny.

1141
01:52:24.452 --> 01:52:27.728
FBI. That call from J Edgar Hoover
was for me.

1142
01:52:30.372 --> 01:52:32.602
I told you I didn't do it.

1143
01:52:38.772 --> 01:52:41.286
- All right. Who done it?
- He did it.

1144
01:52:41.452 --> 01:52:43.204
- That gentleman...
- No!

1145
01:52:43.372 --> 01:52:45.488
They all did it.

1146
01:52:46.572 --> 01:52:50.167
But if you wanna know
who killed Mr Boddy. I did.

1147
01:52:50.332 --> 01:52:53.642
In the hall. with the revolver.

1148
01:52:53.812 --> 01:52:57.930
OK. chief. Take 'em away.
I'm going home to sleep with my wife.

1149
01:56:26.163 --> 01:56:31.362
- Didn't mean to frighten you.
- Bit late for that... I hate that!

1150
01:56:31.523 --> 01:56:36.438
Then came three more murders.
None of us killed Mr Boddy or the cook.

1151
01:56:36.603 --> 01:56:39.993
- So who did?!
- The one person who wasn't with us.

1152
01:56:42.163 --> 01:56:43.994
- Yvette.
- Yvette!

1153
01:56:44.163 --> 01:56:48.793
She was listening to us. She heard
the shot and thought he was dead.

1154
01:56:48.963 --> 01:56:53.400
While we examined the bullet-hole.
she got the dagger. ran to the kitchen.

1155
01:56:53.563 --> 01:56:58.956
and stabbed the cook. We heard nothing
because Mrs Peacock was screaming.

1156
01:56:59.123 --> 01:57:02.320
Yvette returned.
screamed and we ran to her.

1157
01:57:02.483 --> 01:57:05.361
- When did she kill Mr Boddy?
- When I said.

1158
01:57:05.523 --> 01:57:10.119
We ran to see the cook. Yvette
checked that Mr Boddy was dead.

1159
01:57:10.283 --> 01:57:15.880
He followed into the hall. she hit him on
the head and dragged him to the toilet.

1160
01:57:16.043 --> 01:57:18.159
- Why?
- To create confusion.

1161
01:57:18.323 --> 01:57:20.917
- It worked.
- Why did she do it?

1162
01:57:21.083 --> 01:57:25.235
Was she obeying orders
from the person who later killed her?

1163
01:57:25.403 --> 01:57:26.722
- Who?
- Who?

1164
01:57:26.883 --> 01:57:28.680
Who?

1165
01:57:28.843 --> 01:57:32.552
Was it one of her clients?

1166
01:57:32.723 --> 01:57:37.433
Or was it a jealous wife?
Or an adulterous doctor?

1167
01:57:37.603 --> 01:57:41.915
- No. it was her employer. miss Scarlet.
- That's a lie.

1168
01:57:42.083 --> 01:57:46.474
Is it? You used her
the way you always used her.

1169
01:57:46.643 --> 01:57:48.793
You killed the motorist.

1170
01:57:48.963 --> 01:57:52.717
- How did I know about the passage?
- Yvette told you.

1171
01:57:52.883 --> 01:57:58.276
When we split up again.
you switched off the electricity.

1172
01:57:58.443 --> 01:58:02.277
You got the lead pipe and the rope.
strangled Yvette.

1173
01:58:02.443 --> 01:58:07.471
ran to the library. killed the cop.
picked up the gun.

1174
01:58:07.643 --> 01:58:13.639
opened the door. recognised the singer
from her photo. and shot her.

1175
01:58:13.803 --> 01:58:17.000
- You've no proof.
- The gun is missing.

1176
01:58:17.163 --> 01:58:21.236
Gentlemen. turn out your pockets.
Ladies. empty your purses.

1177
01:58:21.403 --> 01:58:23.917
Whoever has the gun is the murderer.

1178
01:58:25.003 --> 01:58:27.312
Brilliant! I congratulate you.

1179
01:58:27.483 --> 01:58:29.872
- Me too!
- Shut up!

1180
01:58:30.043 --> 01:58:32.955
- One thing I don't understand.
- One thing?

1181
01:58:33.123 --> 01:58:36.274
Why? Half of Washington
knows your business.

1182
01:58:36.443 --> 01:58:40.675
You were in no danger. The whole town
would be implicated with you.

1183
01:58:40.843 --> 01:58:45.314
They don't know
that my real business is secrets.

1184
01:58:45.483 --> 01:58:47.951
And Yvette found them out for me.

1185
01:58:48.123 --> 01:58:51.433
The secrets of Senator Peacock's
defence committee.

1186
01:58:51.603 --> 01:58:57.599
Colonel Mustard's fusion bomb.
Professor Plum's UN contacts.

1187
01:58:57.763 --> 01:59:02.996
and the work of your husband.
the nuclear physicist.

1188
01:59:03.163 --> 01:59:05.996
So. it is political. You're a communist!

1189
01:59:06.163 --> 01:59:10.122
No. Mr Green.
Communism is just a red herring.

1190
01:59:10.283 --> 01:59:14.993
Like all prostitutes. I'm a capitalist
and I'm going to sell my secrets.

1191
01:59:15.163 --> 01:59:18.155
your secrets. to the highest bidder.

1192
01:59:18.323 --> 01:59:23.033
- What if we don't cooperate?
- You will. or I'll expose you.

1193
01:59:23.203 --> 01:59:29.039
- We could expose you. Six murders...
- It won't help your reputation at the UN.

1194
01:59:29.203 --> 01:59:33.833
You're implicated not only in adultery
with a patient but in her death.

1195
01:59:34.003 --> 01:59:39.600
- And the deaths of five others.
- You don't know the UN. it might help.

1196
01:59:39.763 --> 01:59:44.473
- It's no good. I've no more money.
- Neither do I.

1197
01:59:44.643 --> 01:59:49.956
I know. But you can pay me
in government information. all of you.

1198
01:59:51.083 --> 01:59:53.313
Except you. Wadsworth.

1199
01:59:53.483 --> 01:59:57.874
As a butler. you have no access
to government secrets.

1200
01:59:58.043 --> 02:00:01.115
So. I'm afraid your moment has come.

1201
02:00:01.283 --> 02:00:04.992
- Not so fast! I do have a secret or two.
- Such as?

1202
02:00:05.163 --> 02:00:08.041
Game's up.
There are no bullets in that gun.

1203
02:00:08.203 --> 02:00:11.354
- I'm not falling for that trick.
- It's no trick.

1204
02:00:11.523 --> 02:00:16.119
One for Boddy. two for the chandelier.
two at the door and one for the singer.

1205
02:00:16.283 --> 02:00:19.480
- That's not six.
- One plus two plus two plus one.

1206
02:00:19.643 --> 02:00:22.555
One for the chandelier.
One plus two plus one plus one.

1207
02:00:22.723 --> 02:00:27.922
That's one plus one plus two plus one.
Not one plus two plus one plus one.

1208
02:00:28.083 --> 02:00:30.313
One plus two plus... shut up!

1209
02:00:30.483 --> 02:00:34.681
The point is. there's one bullet.
and guess who's gonna get it?

1210
02:00:44.763 --> 02:00:47.721
I'm only a guest!

1211
02:00:49.283 --> 02:00:51.956
Where's the chief?

1212
02:00:52.683 --> 02:00:54.833
Well done. Wadsworth.

1213
02:00:55.003 --> 02:00:59.474
I warned you. Mr Hoover
is an expert on Armageddon.

1214
02:00:59.643 --> 02:01:02.601
Don't hate me for trying to shoot you.

1215
02:01:02.763 --> 02:01:07.632
Frankly. Scarlet. I don't give a damn.
There are no bullets in this gun.

1216
02:01:12.163 --> 02:01:15.314
One plus two... plus one...

1217
02:01:15.483 --> 02:01:18.441
Plus two. plus one... is...
